{"type":"message","id":"2aa58bc7","parentId":"360dfa84","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:40:41.226Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-06 10:40 EST] # Prompt for MAIN Agent \n\n## Task: Hardening and Automation Upgrade — `error-learning-loop` \n\n \n\nYou are the **MAIN orchestration agent**. \n\n \n\nYour task is to spawn a **specialized sub-agent session** to enhance the existing skill: \n\n \n\nskills/error-learning-loop \n\n \n\nThe goal is to make the learning system **fully autonomous**, reducing the need for manual intervention when processing incidents. \n\n \n\nThe upgrade must implement a **dual execution strategy**: \n\n \n\n1. Event‑Driven Learning (Primary) \n\n2. Scheduled Reconciliation (Backup via Cron) \n\n \n\nBoth must coexist to guarantee system reliability. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Objective \n\n \n\nEnsure the `error-learning-loop` can: \n\n \n\n• Automatically capture incidents from all skills \n\n• Process incidents into Pattern‑Keys \n\n• Deduplicate semantically \n\n• Promote guardrails when patterns repeat \n\n• Update INDEX.md and REPORT.md automatically \n\n• Detect and process incidents that were missed by triggers \n\n \n\nThe system must work **without manual invocation**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Current Limitations to Address \n\n \n\nThe system currently depends on: \n\n \n\n• Manual processing of incidents \n\n• Handoff Reports that may be missing or incomplete \n\n• Skills that sometimes emit unstructured errors \n\n• Partial Pattern‑Key coverage \n\n \n\nThese gaps must be resolved. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Architecture Upgrade \n\n \n\nImplement a **two‑layer automation model**: \n\n \n\nLayer 1 — Event‑Driven Processing \n\nLayer 2 — Scheduled Reconciliation (Cron) \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Layer 1 — Event‑Driven Processing (Primary) \n\n \n\nThe system must trigger learning automatically whenever any of the following occurs: \n\n \n\n• A sub‑agent finishes execution \n\n• A Handoff Report contains incidents \n\n• agent-watchdog detects stall or deadlock \n\n• A skill writes to `.learnings/ERRORS.md` \n\n• A complex task finishes execution \n\n \n\nRequired flow: \n\n \n\nemit_incident() \n\n→ append .learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n→ trigger error-learning-loop \n\n→ rebuild INDEX.md \n\n→ update REPORT.md \n\n \n\nAll skills must call a **unified incident interface**. \n\n \n\nExample interface: \n\n \n\nemit_incident( \n\npattern_key, \n\nseverity, \n\nsource_skill, \n\ndescription, \n\nevidence \n\n) \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Layer 2 — Scheduled Reconciliation (Cron Backup) \n\n \n\nA scheduled job must run daily to ensure **no incidents remain unprocessed**. \n\n \n\nRecommended schedule: \n\n \n\nMonday–Friday \n\n1:30 PM Panama Time \n\n \n\nThe cron task must: \n\n \n\n1. Scan `.learnings/ERRORS.md` \n\n2. Detect incidents not yet processed \n\n3. Detect Pattern‑Keys missing from INDEX.md \n\n4. Rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md \n\n5. Promote new guardrails if thresholds are met \n\n6. Generate a reconciliation summary \n\n \n\nThe cron job must **never overwrite previous learning history**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Incident Coverage Expansion \n\n \n\nExtend Pattern‑Key coverage for common system issues: \n\n \n\nModel Stalls \n\nruntime|STALL|model|no_response \n\n \n\nDeadlocks \n\nruntime|DEADLOCK|multi_agent|dependency_cycle \n\n \n\nFIT/GAP failures \n\nfitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify \n\n \n\nToken overflow \n\ntokens|OVERFLOW|context_window|exceeded \n\n \n\nCheckpoint failures \n\nrecovery|FAILURE|checkpoint_missing \n\n \n\nSecurity violations \n\nsecurity|FLS_MISSING|apex \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Guardrail Promotion Policy \n\n \n\nA learning should be promoted to guardrail when: \n\n \n\n• It appears 2 or more times \n\n• OR severity is High \n\n• OR it causes system instability \n\n \n\nGuardrails must be written to: \n\n \n\nAGENTS.md \n\nTOOLS.md \n\n \n\nEach guardrail must include: \n\n \n\n• Prevention rule \n\n• Trigger condition \n\n• Preflight check \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Handoff Report Enforcement \n\n \n\nEvery sub‑agent must produce a structured handoff report including: \n\n \n\nOutcome \n\nFiles created \n\nIncidents detected \n\nNext recommended actions \n\n \n\nIf a sub‑agent finishes without a valid report: \n\n \n\nhandoff|INVALID|missing_report \n\n \n\nmust be emitted automatically. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Orphan Incident Detection \n\n \n\nThe cron reconciliation must detect: \n\n \n\n• Incidents present in ERRORS.md but not in INDEX.md \n\n• Pattern‑Keys without guardrails \n\n• Repeated incidents without promotion \n\n \n\nThese must be processed automatically. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Required Implementation \n\n \n\nThe sub-agent must extend the skill with: \n\n \n\nscripts/emit_incident.py \n\nscripts/event_trigger_listener.py \n\nscripts/reconcile_incidents.py \n\nscripts/cron_reconciliation_runner.py \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Expected Behavior \n\n \n\nAfter implementation: \n\n \n\n• Incident learning occurs automatically \n\n• Missed incidents are recovered by the daily reconciliation \n\n• Guardrails evolve without manual intervention \n\n• The learning system becomes self‑maintaining \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Validation \n\n \n\nRun a validation simulation: \n\n \n\n1. Inject incidents into `.learnings/ERRORS.md` \n\n2. Verify automatic learning trigger \n\n3. Disable trigger temporarily \n\n4. Confirm cron reconciliation processes the missed incidents \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Final Output Required \n\n \n\nReturn a **Handoff Report** containing: \n\n \n\nOutcome \n\nAutomation mechanisms implemented \n\nCron configuration \n\nFiles created \n\nValidation results"}],"timestamp":1772811641218}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5538672","parentId":"2aa58bc7","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:40:49.173Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to spawn a specialized sub-agent to enhance the error-learning-loop skill. First, I should check the existing skill structure to understand current implementation. Let's read the SKILL.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_qboTqZNR6ljzVswFtMxzktka","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":15160,"output":137,"cacheRead":1984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17281,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772811641222}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0d782ff","parentId":"d5538672","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:40:49.206Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_qboTqZNR6ljzVswFtMxzktka","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: error-learning-loop\ndescription: Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# error-learning-loop\n\n## Purpose\nCreate a structured feedback loop where the **main agent** learns from:\n- its own errors/near-misses, and\n- **sub-agent handoff reports** (Option 1: chat-based reporting),\nso repeated mistakes become guardrails in the workspace.\n\nThis skill is designed to be installed **only in the main agent workspace**.\n\n## Operating Modes\n### Manual Mode\nTriggered explicitly by the user.\n\nExample:\n\"Run the learning loop.\"\n\n### Wrap-Up Mode\nExecuted at the end of a task **ONLY IF** at least one incident occurred:\n- tool failure / exception / non-zero exit\n- user correction or new requirement that invalidates prior work\n- near-miss detected\n- sub-agent handoff indicates failure/partial or an incident\n\nIf no incident occurred, wrap-up should not execute.\n\n## Multi-agent data source (Option 1 — REQUIRED)\nThe main agent must collect incidents from sub-agents via a mandatory **Handoff Report** appended to every sub-agent’s final response.\n\n### Handoff Report (required format)\nSub-agents must end with:\n\nOutcome: success|partial|failure\nIncidents:\n- [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <symptom in 1 line> (evidence: <1 line, no secrets>)\nPattern hint: <optional, 1 line>\nPrevention rule: <optional, 1 line>\nFiles touched: <list or \"none\">\nNext action: <1 line>\n\n### Rules for sub-agents\n- Do NOT include secrets/tokens/credentials.\n- Keep evidence brief and concrete.\n- If there were no incidents: set Outcome=success and Incidents: none.\n\n## Core Concept: Semantic Dedupe\nTraditional dedupe compares exact strings.\nSemantic dedupe groups incidents by **meaning** into stable Pattern-Keys.\n\nExample (all same semantic class):\n- \"rg command not found\"\n- \"ripgrep missing\"\n- \"bash failed because rg not installed\"\n→ Pattern-Key: tools|TOOL_FAILURE|bash|missing_binary|binary_not_in_path\n\n## Pattern-Key\nFormat:\n<domain>|<type>|<tool>|<failure_class>|<root_cause_signature>\n\n## Hard Safety Rules (non-negotiable)\n1) Only read/write inside the current workspace and {baseDir}. Never edit outside.\n2) Never store secrets, tokens, passwords, keys, or private identifiers in learnings/logs.\n3) Do NOT install dependencies; do NOT auto-refactor code; do NOT change global OpenClaw config.\n4) Session/history access (if available) is allowed only when invoked and only for relevant sessions.\n5) Prefer minimal, auditable edits: small diffs, clear headings, and dated entries.\n6) If unsure whether something is sensitive: redact it.\n\n## Mitigations (to prevent common failure modes)\n### M1 — Prevent overfitting (bad generalizations)\nPromote a learning to AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md only if it is generalizable AND:\n- repeated Pattern-Key occurrences >= 2, OR\n- Severity is S1/S2 structural issue.\n\nOtherwise keep it in .learnings only.\n\n### M2 — Prevent logging noise\nKeep entries concise:\n- Symptoms: max 6 bullets\n- Root Cause: max 4 bullets\n- 1 learning sentence\n- 1 prevention rule\n- Preflight: 2–6 checks max\n\n### M3 — Prevent sensitive-data leakage\nBefore writing:\n- redact tokens/keys/passwords\n- replace emails/phones with placeholders\n- avoid customer names unless explicitly required\n\n### M4 — Prevent uncontrolled scope creep\nIf the fix requires new capability:\n- log as FEATURE_REQUEST\n- do not implement automatically\n\n## Inputs\nFrom current context:\n- Task goal (1–2 sentences)\n- Evidence: tool outputs, user corrections\n- Tags (mandatory):\n  - agent=<name>\n  - session=<id>\n  - task=<short>\n\nFrom sub-agents (required):\n- Handoff Report blocks (as provided in chat)\n\nOptional (only for dedupe confirmation):\n- Minimal relevant session history snippets (if tools exist)\n\n## Outputs\nAlways update at least one:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n\nSometimes:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n- Workspace patches (minimal):\n  - `<workspace>/AGENTS.md`\n  - `<workspace>/TOOLS.md`\n\n**New mandatory output** (added in this version):\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md` – consolidated index of Pattern‑Keys, guardrails, and trends. Must be updated and deduplicated after every learning‑loop run.\n\n## Step-by-step instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Ensure learning store exists\nCreate if missing:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n\n### Step 1 — Detect incidents (wrap-up gate)\nIf running wrap-up:\n- Confirm at least one incident occurred (from main execution or sub-agent handoff).\n- If none: STOP. No logging.\n\n### Step 2 — Collect evidence (main + sub-agents)\nFrom the main task:\n- what we attempted\n- what happened\n- root cause hypothesis\n- what fixed it\n\nFrom sub-agents:\n- parse each Handoff Report\n- extract Outcome + each Incident line\n- discard/redact anything sensitive\n\n### Step 3 — Generate Semantic Pattern-Key\nFor each incident:\n- normalize into a stable Pattern-Key using:\n  domain + type + tool (if any) + failure_class + root_cause_signature\n\n### Step 4 — Semantic Deduplication\nCompare against existing Pattern-Keys in:\n- .learnings/ERRORS.md\n- .learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n\nIf a semantically matching Pattern-Key exists:\n- increment Count\n- update Last Seen\n- append an Occurrence entry\n\nElse:\n- create a new entry\n\n### Step 5 — Extract Learning\nFor each (new or repeated) Pattern-Key:\n- 1 learning statement\n- 1 prevention rule\n- optional preflight checklist (tools-related only)\n\n### Step 6 — Promotion\nApply Mitigation M1.\nPromote:\n- workflow/coordination guardrails → AGENTS.md (\"## Guardrails (Auto-learnings)\")\n- tool-specific guardrails → TOOLS.md (\"## Tool Guardrails\")\n\nEdits must include:\n- date\n- Pattern-Key\n- rule (+ preflight if any)\n\n### Step 7 — Close\nAdd an applied note:\nApplied: yes/no\nPromoted to: AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none\nNext time: expected behavior\n\n### Step 8 — Update Learning Retrieval Index\n\n**Purpose**:\nMaintain a lightweight retrieval index so the agent can quickly find relevant Pattern‑Keys without scanning full logs.\n\n**Actions**:\n\n1. Read:\n   - `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n   - `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n\n2. Extract all Pattern‑Keys and derive:\n   - domain\n   - tags (3–6)\n   - rule (one line)\n   - promoted_to (AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none)\n\n3. Read:\n   - `AGENTS.md`\n   - `TOOLS.md`\n   to detect promoted guardrails.\n\n4. Rebuild `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md` from scratch with fixed domain sections.\n\n5. Deduplicate Pattern‑Keys globally.\n\n6. Ensure each entry contains at most 3–4 short lines.\n\n7. Write analytics and trend information to `<workspace>/.learnings/REPORT.md`.\n\n## Example usage\nManual:\n\"Run the learning loop using the sub-agent handoff reports from this task.\"\nWrap-up:\nIf incidents occurred, run Steps 2–8; otherwise skip.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772811649203}}
