{"type":"message","id":"0f7b114b","parentId":"886a0fb7","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:41:14.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_KuVbqWa3utXmtrjA85OkH25e","toolName":"agents_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"requester\": \"main\",\n  \"allowAny\": false,\n  \"agents\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"main\",\n      \"configured\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"requester":"main","allowAny":false,"agents":[{"id":"main","configured":true}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772811674024}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b21111d","parentId":"0f7b114b","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:41:25.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only main. That's fine, we can spawn a sub-agent with runtime \"subagent\" using agentId \"main\". However, we need to consider guardrails about DeepSeek reasoning mode and model stall prevention. The sub-agent will likely run a longer task, so we should avoid reasoning mode. Let's use the default model (DeepSeek-reasoner) but without reasoning mode? Actually reasoning is off by default. We'll set model to \"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-reasoner\" (default). We'll also need to register with watchdog. I'll spawn the sub-agent with a clear task description.\n\nBut first, let's check if there is a watchdog skill to understand registration procedure. Let's read its SKILL.md:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XY5gzyRYVB0GutsMNg9UPGeS","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":176,"output":372,"cacheRead":19968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20516,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772811674028}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6bf4b90","parentId":"5b21111d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:41:25.472Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_XY5gzyRYVB0GutsMNg9UPGeS","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts.\n- Never restart agents indefinitely.\n- Always emit incident report.\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772811685469}}
{"type":"message","id":"f108b4f8","parentId":"b6bf4b90","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:42:51.194Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now we need to spawn the sub-agent. Let's craft the task prompt. We'll include the handoff report requirement. Let's also note that we need to register the sub-agent with watchdog. However, we can't run the watchdog registration script from within the sub-agent's prompt? Actually we can ask the sub-agent to register itself with watchdog after spawning? That's a bit meta. Better to register after spawning from main. I'll do that after spawning. But first, let's spawn the sub-agent. Use sessions_spawn with runtime subagent, agentId main, label \"error-learning-loop-upgrade\". Let's write the task prompt:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ALAtxLl7AB3RiPJeH34cHM8Z","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Hardening and Automation Upgrade for `error-learning-loop` skill\n\nYou are a specialized sub-agent tasked with enhancing the existing skill located at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop`. The goal is to make the learning system **fully autonomous**, reducing the need for manual intervention when processing incidents.\n\nYou must implement a **dual execution strategy**:\n1. Event‑Driven Learning (Primary)\n2. Scheduled Reconciliation (Backup via Cron)\n\nBoth must coexist to guarantee system reliability.\n\n## Current Skill Structure\n- SKILL.md defines manual and wrap-up modes.\n- Scripts directory currently contains only `update_index.py`.\n- Learning store at `~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/` includes ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, REPORT.md, FEATURE_REQUESTS.md.\n\n## Objective\nEnsure the `error-learning-loop` can:\n- Automatically capture incidents from all skills\n- Process incidents into Pattern‑Keys\n- Deduplicate semantically\n- Promote guardrails when patterns repeat\n- Update INDEX.md and REPORT.md automatically\n- Detect and process incidents that were missed by triggers\n\n## Architecture Upgrade\nImplement a **two‑layer automation model**:\n\n### Layer 1 — Event‑Driven Processing (Primary)\nThe system must trigger learning automatically whenever any of the following occurs:\n- A sub‑agent finishes execution\n- A Handoff Report contains incidents\n- agent-watchdog detects stall or deadlock\n- A skill writes to `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- A complex task finishes execution\n\nRequired flow:\nemit_incident()\n→ append .learnings/ERRORS.md\n→ trigger error-learning-loop\n→ rebuild INDEX.md\n→ update REPORT.md\n\nAll skills must call a **unified incident interface**.\n\nExample interface:\nemit_incident(\n  pattern_key,\n  severity,\n  source_skill,\n  description,\n  evidence\n)\n\nYou need to create:\n- `scripts/emit_incident.py` – unified incident emitter that writes to ERRORS.md and triggers learning loop (if event-driven mode enabled).\n- `scripts/event_trigger_listener.py` – a script that can be invoked by other skills to register incidents and trigger processing. It should also handle automatic invocation when Handoff Reports are detected (maybe via a wrapper function). For simplicity, we can make emit_incident also call the learning loop directly (by importing existing functions from update_index.py). However, we need to avoid circular imports. Consider refactoring common logic into a shared module.\n\n### Layer 2 — Scheduled Reconciliation (Cron Backup)\nA scheduled job must run daily to ensure **no incidents remain unprocessed**.\n\nRecommended schedule: Monday–Friday at 1:30 PM Panama Time (America/Panama).\n\nThe cron task must:\n1. Scan `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n2. Detect incidents not yet processed (i.e., those missing from INDEX.md)\n3. Detect Pattern‑Keys missing from INDEX.md\n4. Rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md\n5. Promote new guardrails if thresholds are met\n6. Generate a reconciliation summary\n\nThe cron job must **never overwrite previous learning history**.\n\nCreate:\n- `scripts/reconcile_incidents.py` – scans ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, identifies unprocessed incidents, and runs the learning loop on them.\n- `scripts/cron_reconciliation_runner.py` – wrapper that sets up environment and calls reconcile_incidents.py; also logs start/end times.\n\n## Incident Coverage Expansion\nExtend Pattern‑Key coverage for common system issues (add to pattern key mapping):\n- Model Stalls: `runtime|STALL|model|no_response`\n- Deadlocks: `runtime|DEADLOCK|multi_agent|dependency_cycle`\n- FIT/GAP failures: `fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify`\n- Token overflow: `tokens|OVERFLOW|context_window|exceeded`\n- Checkpoint failures: `recovery|FAILURE|checkpoint_missing`\n- Security violations: `security|FLS_MISSING|apex`\n\nEnsure these patterns are recognized during semantic deduplication.\n\n## Guardrail Promotion Policy\nA learning should be promoted to guardrail when:\n- It appears 2 or more times\n- OR severity is High\n- OR it causes system instability\n\nGuardrails must be written to AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md.\n\nEach guardrail must include:\n- Prevention rule\n- Trigger condition\n- Preflight check\n\n## Handoff Report Enforcement\nEvery sub‑agent must produce a structured handoff report. If a sub‑agent finishes without a valid report, emit incident `handoff|INVALID|missing_report` automatically.\n\nImplement detection in the event-driven layer: after sub-agent session ends, check its final message for handoff report format; if missing, call emit_incident.\n\n## Orphan Incident Detection\nThe cron reconciliation must detect:\n- Incidents present in ERRORS.md but not in INDEX.md\n- Pattern‑Keys without guardrails\n- Repeated incidents without promotion\n\n## Implementation Steps\n1. Examine existing `update_index.py` to understand current deduplication and indexing logic. Refactor reusable functions into a shared module (e.g., `scripts/common.py`).\n2. Create `emit_incident.py` with function `emit_incident(pattern_key, severity, source_skill, description, evidence)` that appends to ERRORS.md and optionally triggers learning loop (if event-driven mode). It should also call a trigger script that runs the learning loop asynchronously (maybe via subprocess). However, to avoid complexity, we can have emit_incident simply write to ERRORS.md and let a separate daemon process trigger learning loop. But we don't have a daemon. Simpler: emit_incident will call the learning loop directly via importing the processing functions. Ensure idempotency.\n3. Create `event_trigger_listener.py` that can be invoked by other skills (e.g., agent-watchdog) to emit incidents. It can also be used as a CLI tool.\n4. Create `reconcile_incidents.py` that reads ERRORS.md, extracts incidents, checks against INDEX.md, processes missing ones.\n5. Create `cron_reconciliation_runner.py` that logs and calls reconcile_incidents.py.\n6. Update SKILL.md to document the new automation features and how to integrate with other skills.\n7. Provide example integration code for other skills (e.g., agent-watchdog) to call emit_incident.\n8. Test the system by injecting sample incidents and verifying automatic learning trigger and cron reconciliation.\n\n## Validation\nRun a validation simulation:\n1. Inject incidents into `.learnings/ERRORS.md` (simulate missed incidents).\n2. Verify automatic learning trigger (by calling emit_incident).\n3. Disable trigger temporarily (rename scripts) and confirm cron reconciliation processes the missed incidents.\n\n## Notes\n- Maintain safety rules: never edit outside workspace, redact secrets.\n- Keep changes minimal and auditable.\n- Ensure backward compatibility: existing manual and wrap-up modes must still work.\n\n## Deliverables\n- New scripts as described.\n- Updated SKILL.md with documentation for automation.\n- Example integration snippet.\n- Validation results.\n\n## Mandatory Final Block\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report using this exact format:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <brief symptom> (evidence: <1‑line concrete detail, no secrets>)\n  - Pattern hint: <optional>\n  - Prevention rule: <optional>\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp of last progress>\n  - progress_marker: <current step or checkpoint>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".","label":"error-learning-loop-upgrade","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1170,"output":2114,"cacheRead":20096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23380,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772811685472}}
