{"type":"message","id":"6dcc7736","parentId":"a66caeac","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:44:43.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now we can wait a bit and check for new messages. Since we're in webchat, we'll get a notification when sub-agent completes. Let's just keep the session alive. Let's also maybe read the sub-agent's progress by checking its session history? We can use sessions_history but that's polling; we shouldn't poll. However, we can check once after a few minutes to see if there is any output. But we can also just wait.\n\nLet's take a moment to think about the overall task. The sub-agent is expected to implement the automation upgrade. That's a lot of work; we should ensure it has enough time. The expected runtime we set 30 minutes may be insufficient. Let's adjust by sending a steer message to increase timeout? Actually we can't change runtime after spawn. But we can send a \"continue\" message if it times out. Let's wait.\n\nMeanwhile, we can also examine the error-learning-loop skill's update_index.py to understand the current deduplication logic. Let's read it:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HjyxxC2knc2rLFFzLPhqUspk","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py","limit":100}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":374,"output":501,"cacheRead":32000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32875,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772811868487}}
{"type":"message","id":"8db5e889","parentId":"6dcc7736","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:44:43.346Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_HjyxxC2knc2rLFFzLPhqUspk","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nupdate_index.py – Rebuild INDEX.md (lightweight retrieval index) and REPORT.md (analytics)\nfrom ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, AGENTS.md, and TOOLS.md.\n\nINDEX.md is minimal, grouped by fixed domain sections, each entry 3–4 lines.\nREPORT.md contains summary, tables, trends, and promotion stats.\n\nPattern‑Keys are deduplicated globally (keep highest count, newest last seen).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n# Fixed domain sections (in order)\nDOMAIN_SECTIONS = [\n    \"tools\",\n    \"requirements\",\n    \"planning\",\n    \"multi-agent\",\n    \"validation\",\n    \"other\"\n]\n\ndef classify_domain(pattern_key):\n    \"\"\"Map Pattern‑Key's first segment to a fixed domain section.\"\"\"\n    if '|' not in pattern_key:\n        return \"other\"\n    first = pattern_key.split('|')[0].strip().lower()\n    # Direct mapping for known domains\n    if first == \"validation\":\n        return \"validation\"\n    if first == \"multi_agent\":\n        return \"multi-agent\"\n    if first in (\"model\", \"tool\", \"tools\", \"exec\", \"browser\", \"web\", \"tts\", \"image\", \"pdf\"):\n        return \"tools\"\n    if first in (\"requirement\", \"requirements\", \"spec\", \"specification\"):\n        return \"requirements\"\n    if first in (\"plan\", \"planning\", \"strategy\", \"design\"):\n        return \"planning\"\n    return \"other\"\n\ndef generate_tags(pattern_key, learning_entry):\n    \"\"\"Produce 3–6 contextual tags from Pattern‑Key, focused on tool/domain/action.\"\"\"\n    parts = [p.strip() for p in pattern_key.split('|') if p.strip()]\n    tags = set()\n    \n    # Helper to split snake_case into words and add meaningful ones\n    def add_meaningful(text, exclude_generic=True):\n        words = text.lower().split('_')\n        generic = {\"error\", \"failure\", \"handoff\", \"missing\", \"required\", \"content\", \n                   \"field\", \"report\", \"contract\", \"enforced\", \"excessive\", \"workload\",\n                   \"timeout\", \"unknown\", \"none\", \"openclaw\", \"not\", \"and\", \"or\", \"but\",\n                   \"for\", \"with\", \"without\", \"from\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"at\", \"by\", \"as\",\n                   \"if\", \"then\", \"else\", \"when\", \"where\", \"how\", \"why\", \"what\", \"which\",\n                   \"who\", \"whom\", \"whose\", \"this\", \"that\", \"these\", \"those\", \"there\", \"here\",\n                   \"been\", \"being\", \"have\", \"has\", \"had\", \"do\", \"does\", \"did\", \"will\", \"would\",\n                   \"should\", \"could\", \"may\", \"might\", \"must\", \"can\", \"cannot\"}\n        for w in words:\n            if not w or len(w) < 3:\n                continue\n            if exclude_generic and w in generic:\n                continue\n            tags.add(w)\n    \n    # Domain (first part) - add normalized (underscores to hyphens)\n    if len(parts) > 0:\n        domain = parts[0].lower()\n        if domain not in (\"unknown\", \"none\"):\n            # Normalize underscores to hyphens for consistency\n            domain_norm = domain.replace('_', '-')\n            tags.add(domain_norm)\n    \n    # Type (second part) - map to more descriptive tags\n    if len(parts) > 1:\n        typ = parts[1].lower()\n        # Map generic types to more specific concepts\n        type_map = {\n            \"error\": \"model-error\",\n            \"tool_failure\": \"tool-failure\",\n            \"multi_agent_handoff\": \"multi-agent\"\n        }\n        if typ in type_map:\n            tags.add(type_map[typ])\n        else:\n            add_meaningful(typ, exclude_generic=True)\n    \n    # Tool (third part) - extract tool name, strip prefixes\n    if len(parts) > 2:\n        tool = parts[2].lower()\n        if tool.startswith(\"openclaw_\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"openclaw_\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_reasoner\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"_reasoner\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_validator\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"_validator\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_subagent\"):\n\n[402 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772811883341}}
