{"type":"message","id":"faa141fd","parentId":"6d25d78a","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:46:31.684Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_JXoRlacmC0mL4rWrvf4y805p","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\ndef generate_incident(model, stall_duration, recovery_level, success,\n                      runtime_type='subagent', task_type='unknown', items_count=0):\n    \"\"\"Generate stall incident telemetry.\"\"\"\n    if runtime_type == 'acp':\n        pattern_key = f\"runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck\"\n    else:\n        pattern_key = f\"model|STALL|{model}|no_response|runtime_stuck\"\n    \n    return {\n        \"pattern_key\": pattern_key,\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"model\": model,\n        \"stall_duration\": stall_duration,\n        \"recovery_level\": recovery_level,\n        \"success\": success,\n        \"runtime_type\": runtime_type,\n        \"task_type\": task_type,\n        \"items_count\": items_count\n    }\n\ndef generate_deadlock_incident(cycle, recovery_strategy, success):\n    \"\"\"Generate deadlock incident telemetry.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"pattern_key\": \"multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting\",\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"cycle_size\": len(cycle),\n        \"agents_involved\": cycle,\n        \"recovery_strategy\": recovery_strategy,\n        \"success\": success\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772811991678}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c38c7e3","parentId":"faa141fd","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:46:48.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the watchdog already emits incidents with pattern keys. That's good.\n\nNow we need to ensure the error-learning-loop can be triggered automatically when new incidents are appended. The watchdog currently calls `append_to_errors` with `trigger_learning=True`. That function tries to invoke the skill via `_try_invoke_learning_skill` which currently returns False, then falls back to `_rebuild_index_fallback`. That's just rebuilding index, not full learning loop. That's insufficient. We need to trigger the full learning loop (including guardrail promotion). That's what we need to implement.\n\nThus the sub-agent's automation should provide a way to invoke the learning loop (maybe via spawning a sub-agent that runs the skill). That's what we need to add: a function that spawns the error-learning-loop skill as a sub-agent. That's possible via `sessions_spawn`. We can write a script that uses the OpenClaw CLI? Actually we can use the OpenClaw Gateway API? But we can use the same `sessions_spawn` tool if we are within an agent session. However, a script running outside the agent context (e.g., from cron) cannot call that tool. We need a different approach: maybe we can run the agent with a specific command that triggers the skill. Let's check if there's an `openclaw agent` command that can run a skill. Let's look at `openclaw agent --help`. Let's do a quick exec:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_f63tc4lHbPiVwEdYMEayDNqI","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":509,"output":672,"cacheRead":40832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse"