{"type":"message","id":"7465a026","parentId":"99247dfd","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:49:30.161Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_iWvgc4S7eTNw0yI1xtq4BKFr","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:a98d0427-ea71-40e5-96fc-d7350d0bce09\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\\n\\n[Subagent Task]: ## Task: Hardening and Automation Upgrade for `error-learning-loop` skill\\n\\nYou are a specialized sub-agent tasked with enhancing the existing skill located at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop`. The goal is to make the learning system **fully autonomous**, reducing the need for manual intervention when processing incidents.\\n\\nYou must implement a **dual execution strategy**:\\n1. Event‑Driven Learning (Primary)\\n2. Scheduled Reconciliation (Backup via Cron)\\n\\nBoth must coexist to guarantee system reliability.\\n\\n## Current Skill Structure\\n- SKILL.md defines manual and wrap-up modes.\\n- Scripts directory currently contains only `update_index.py`.\\n- Learning store at `~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/` includes ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, REPORT.md, FEATURE_REQUESTS.md.\\n\\n## Objective\\nEnsure the `error-learning-loop` can:\\n- Automatically capture incidents from all skills\\n- Process incidents into Pattern‑Keys\\n- Deduplicate semantically\\n- Promote guardrails when patterns repeat\\n- Update INDEX.md and REPORT.md automatically\\n- Detect and process incidents that were missed by triggers\\n\\n## Architecture Upgrade\\nImplement a **two‑layer automation model**:\\n\\n### Layer 1 — Event‑Driven Processing (Primary)\\nThe system must trigger learning automatically whenever any of the following occurs:\\n- A sub‑agent finishes execution\\n- A Handoff Report contains incidents\\n- agent-watchdog detects stall or deadlock\\n- A skill writes to `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\\n- A complex task finishes execution\\n\\nRequired flow:\\nemit_incident()\\n→ append .learnings/ERRORS.md\\n→ trigger error-learning-loop\\n→ rebuild INDEX.md\\n→ update REPORT.md\\n\\nAll skills must call a **unified incident interface**.\\n\\nExample interface:\\nemit_incident(\\n  pattern_key,\\n  severity,\\n  source_skill,\\n  description,\\n  evidence\\n)\\n\\nYou need to create:\\n- `scripts/emit_incident.py` – unified incident emitter that writes to ERRORS.md and triggers learning loop (if event-driven mode enabled).\\n- `scripts/event_trigger_listener.py` – a script that can be invoked by other skills to register incidents and trigger processing. It should also handle automatic invocation when Handoff Reports are detected (maybe via a wrapper function). For simplicity, we can make emit_incident also call the learning loop directly (by importing existing functions from update_index.py). However, we need to avoid circular imports. Consider refactoring common logic into a shared module.\\n\\n### Layer 2 — Scheduled Reconciliation (Cron Backup)\\nA scheduled job must run daily to ensure **no incidents remain unprocessed**.\\n\\nRecommended schedule: Monday–Friday at 1:30 PM Panama Time (America/Panama).\\n\\nThe cron task must:\\n1. Scan `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\\n2. Detect incidents not yet processed (i.e., those missing from INDEX.md)\\n3. Detect Pattern‑Keys missing from INDEX.md\\n4. Rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md\\n5. Promote new guardrails if thresholds are met\\n6. Generate a reconciliation summary\\n\\nThe cron job must **never overwrite previous learning history**.\\n\\nCreate:\\n- `scripts/reconcile_incidents.py` – scans ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, identifies unprocessed incidents, and runs the learning loop on them.\\n- `scripts/cron_reconciliation_runner.py` – wrapper that sets up environment and calls reconcile_incidents.py; also logs start/end times.\\n\\n## Incident Coverage Expansion\\nExtend Pattern‑Key coverage for common system issues (add to pattern key mapping):\\n- Model Stalls: `runtime|STALL|model|no_response`\\n- Deadlocks: `runtime|DEADLOCK|multi_agent|dependency_cycle`\\n- FIT/GAP failures: `fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify`\\n- Token overflow: `tokens|OVERFLOW|context_window|exceeded`\\n- Checkpoint failures: `recovery|FAILURE|checkpoint_missing`\\n- Security violations: `security|FLS_MISSING|apex`\\n\\nEnsure these patterns are recognized during semantic deduplication.\\n\\n## Guardrail Promotio\\n…(truncated)…\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811771474\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"I'll start by examining the current skill structure and the existing update_index.py to understand the deduplication logic. First, read the skill's SKILL.md to get the current documentation.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_XykjKTH2eKXRYHRYZolfNyso\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811771476\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now read the existing update_index.py to understand the deduplication and indexing logic.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_VAq3G5WtvqHgI3BfZyiiRAwc\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811779449\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I need to understand the existing structure of ERRORS.md and LEARNINGS.md to know how incidents are formatted. Let's examine the .learnings directory. First, check what's in there:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_rfsPB7qPy1JezLp2CqXwOjks\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811784692\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Look at ERRORS.md format:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_zBB3xIvXh8U9r4eSWDocOfh6\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md\",\n            \"offset\": 1,\n            \"limit\": 50\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811791822\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I have a good understanding. The task is to create new scripts. Let's first refactor common logic into a shared module. I'll create a `scripts/common.py` that contains functions for parsing, deduplication, and writing incidents. We'll need to decide how the event-driven trigger works: we can have emit_incident write to ERRORS.md and then call update_index.py (or import its functions). However, we must avoid circular imports. Let's extract the functions from update_index.py that are needed for processing incidents: parse_errors_md, parse_learnings_md, deduplicate_entries, etc. But maybe we can just call update_index.py as a subprocess after emitting incident? That's simpler and avoids circular imports. However, we need to ensure idempotency: we don't want to run update_index multiple times if many incidents are emitted quickly. Could batch them? For simplicity, we can have emit_incident write to ERRORS.md and then spawn a background process that runs update_index.py after a short delay, or we could just run update_index.py directly each time (since it's lightweight). Might be okay.\\n\\nLet's first examine the existing skill's scripts directory:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_L8aIb7sFe0OL5GPEYKOjZ5lV\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811797379\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now, I'll create common.py with utility functions that both update_index and emit_incident can use. First, let's understand what emit_incident needs: It needs to write a new incident entry into ERRORS.md in the correct format. The format appears to be a new entry under \\\"## Entries\\\" with a heading \\\"### Pattern-Key: ***\\\". However, ERRORS.md currently has a Pattern-Key index table at the top. The update_index.py parses entries but does not write new entries; it only reads. The learning loop (manual or wrap-up) presumably creates new entries in ERRORS.md? Actually, the learning loop writes to ERRORS.md and LEARNINGS.md. That's done by the main skill logic, not by update_index.py. We need to know how incidents are added. Let's look at the skill's main script (maybe there is a learning_loop.py). But there's only update_index.py. Perhaps the skill is invoked via the agent's internal processing, not via a script. The skill is user-invocable, but the actual logic is in the skill's step-by-step instructions in SKILL.md, executed by the agent. That means the agent writes directly to ERRORS.md using its own logic. That's not ideal for automation. We need to provide a script that can be called by other skills to add incidents.\\n\\nThus we need to create a function that appends a new incident to ERRORS.md, creating the appropriate sections if needed. We also need to update the index table? The table is probably generated by update_index.py? Actually, the table in ERRORS.md is also generated by the learning loop? Let's examine the full ERRORS.md to see if the table is manually updated. Let's read the first 100 lines:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_FwRpGD0c6kcSDqDVQD7HSll8\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md\",\n            \"offset\": 1,\n            \"limit\": 100\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811812999\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Interesting. The table at the top appears to be manually updated (maybe by the learning loop). The entries are added with duplicate Pattern-Key lines? I see duplicate Pattern-Key entries for model|STALL|gpt-4... there are two separate entries with same pattern key but different details. That suggests the deduplication is not happening at the ERRORS.md level; maybe the deduplication is done in LEARNINGS.md? Actually, the learning loop deduplicates semantically and updates ERRORS.md with merged entries? Wait, the duplicate entries are separate incidents but same pattern key. That's okay because they are separate occurrences. The index table shows Count = 1 for each? Actually there are multiple entries with same pattern key but each has count 1. The index table maybe aggregates counts? Let's check the index table again: there are only three rows. That means the index table is outdated (maybe not updated after new entries). Indeed the \\\"Updated\\\" date is 2026-03-04, while new entries are from 2026-03-05. So the index table is not being updated automatically. That's a problem. The update_index.py is supposed to update INDEX.md and REPORT.md, but not ERRORS.md's table. The table in ERRORS.md might be generated by the learning loop when it runs (maybe manual). We'll need to decide whether to keep that table or rely on INDEX.md. The SKILL.md says \\\"New mandatory output: INDEX.md\\\". So the table in ERRORS.md is likely legacy. We'll keep the current format for ERRORS.md (entries under ## Entries) and we can just append new entries there. The deduplication and counting will be handled by update_index.py (which reads ERRORS.md and LEARNINGS.md). That's fine.\\n\\nNow we need to design emit_incident.py that appends a new entry to ERRORS.md with the required fields. We'll need to generate a Pattern-Key from the provided parameters? The function will accept pattern_key, severity, source_skill, description, evidence. Also we might need type, symptoms, root cause, fix applied, tags. We can make them optional and default to generic values. The incident should be appended to ERRORS.md, and then we can trigger update_index.py (or call its functions) to update INDEX.md and REPORT.md.\\n\\nWe also need to ensure that we don't duplicate the same incident multiple times (idempotency). We'll maybe generate a hash based on pattern_key + description + evidence + timestamp? Or rely on semantic deduplication later.\\n\\nLet's start by creating common.py with helper functions: read and write ERRORS.md, append entry, maybe deduplicate. We'll also include functions from update_index.py that we need. But we'll keep update_index.py as is and just import its functions if needed. However, we need to avoid circular imports; we can move the parsing functions to common.py and have both scripts import common.\\n\\nLet's first copy the relevant functions from update_index.py into a new common.py. We'll also add a function to append incident.\\n\\nLet's create the scripts directory if not exists. Now I'll write common.py:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_jsAZRarrg3QINNwjfvUBMzwa\",\n          \"name\": \"write\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/common.py\",\n            \"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\ncommon.py – Shared utilities for error-learning-loop scripts.\\nIncludes parsing, deduplication, incident emission, and index generation.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport re\\nimport sys\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\n\\n# Fixed domain sections (in order)\\nDOMAIN_SECTIONS = [\\n    \\\"tools\\\",\\n    \\\"requirements\\\",\\n    \\\"planning\\\",\\n    \\\"multi-agent\\\",\\n    \\\"validation\\\",\\n    \\\"other\\\"\\n]\\n\\ndef classify_domain(pattern_key):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Map Pattern‑Key's first segment to a fixed domain section.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if '|' not in pattern_key:\\n        return \\\"other\\\"\\n    first = pattern_key.split('|')[0].strip().lower()\\n    # Direct mapping for known domains\\n    if first == \\\"validation\\\":\\n        return \\\"validation\\\"\\n    if first == \\\"multi_agent\\\":\\n        return \\\"multi-agent\\\"\\n    if first in (\\\"model\\\", \\\"tool\\\", \\\"tools\\\", \\\"exec\\\", \\\"browser\\\", \\\"web\\\", \\\"tts\\\", \\\"image\\\", \\\"pdf\\\"):\\n        return \\\"tools\\\"\\n    if first in (\\\"requirement\\\", \\\"requirements\\\", \\\"spec\\\", \\\"specification\\\"):\\n        return \\\"requirements\\\"\\n    if first in (\\\"plan\\\", \\\"planning\\\", \\\"strategy\\\", \\\"design\\\"):\\n        return \\\"planning\\\"\\n    return \\\"other\\\"\\n\\ndef generate_tags(pattern_key, learning_entry):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Produce 3–6 contextual tags from Pattern‑Key, focused on tool/domain/action.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    parts = [p.strip() for p in pattern_key.split('|') if p.strip()]\\n    tags = set()\\n    \\n    # Helper to split snake_case into words and add meaningful ones\\n    def add_meaningful(text, exclude_generic=True):\\n        words = text.lower().split('_')\\n        generic = {\\\"error\\\", \\\"failure\\\", \\\"handoff\\\", \\\"missing\\\", \\\"required\\\", \\\"content\\\", \\n                   \\\"field\\\", \\\"report\\\", \\\"contract\\\", \\\"enforced\\\", \\\"excessive\\\", \\\"workload\\\",\\n                   \\\"timeout\\\", \\\"unknown\\\", \\\"none\\\", \\\"openclaw\\\", \\\"not\\\", \\\"and\\\", \\\"or\\\", \\\"but\\\",\\n                   \\\"for\\\", \\\"with\\\", \\\"without\\\", \\\"from\\\", \\\"to\\\", \\\"in\\\", \\\"on\\\", \\\"at\\\", \\\"by\\\", \\\"as\\\",\\n                   \\\"if\\\", \\\"then\\\", \\\"else\\\", \\\"when\\\", \\\"where\\\", \\\"how\\\", \\\"why\\\", \\\"what\\\", \\\"which\\\",\\n                   \\\"who\\\", \\\"whom\\\", \\\"whose\\\", \\\"this\\\", \\\"that\\\", \\\"these\\\", \\\"those\\\", \\\"there\\\", \\\"here\\\",\\n                   \\\"been\\\", \\\"being\\\", \\\"have\\\", \\\"has\\\", \\\"had\\\", \\\"do\\\", \\\"does\\\", \\\"did\\\", \\\"will\\\", \\\"would\\\",\\n                   \\\"should\\\", \\\"could\\\", \\\"may\\\", \\\"might\\\", \\\"must\\\", \\\"can\\\", \\\"cannot\\\"}\\n        for w in words:\\n            if not w or len(w) < 3:\\n                continue\\n            if exclude_generic and w in generic:\\n                continue\\n            tags.add(w)\\n    \\n    # Domain (first part) - add normalized (underscores to hyphens)\\n    if len(parts) > 0:\\n        domain = parts[0].lower()\\n        if domain not in (\\\"unknown\\\", \\\"none\\\"):\\n            # Normalize underscores to hyphens for consistency\\n            domain_norm = domain.replace('_', '-')\\n            tags.add(domain_norm)\\n    \\n    # Type (second part) - map to more descriptive tags\\n    if len(parts) > 1:\\n        typ = parts[1].lower()\\n        # Map generic types to more specific concepts\\n        type_map = {\\n            \\\"error\\\": \\\"model-error\\\",\\n            \\\"tool_failure\\\": \\\"tool-failure\\\",\\n            \\\"multi_agent_handoff\\\": \\\"multi-agent\\\"\\n        }\\n        if typ in type_map:\\n            tags.add(type_map[typ])\\n        else:\\n            add_meaningful(typ, exclude_generic=True)\\n    \\n    # Tool (third part) - extract tool name, strip prefixes\\n    if len(parts) > 2:\\n        tool = parts[2].lower()\\n        if tool.startswith(\\\"openclaw_\\\"):\\n            tool = tool.replace(\\\"openclaw_\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        if tool.endswith(\\\"_reasoner\\\"):\\n            tool = tool.replace(\\\"_reasoner\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        if tool.endswith(\\\"_validator\\\"):\\n            tool = tool.replace(\\\"_validator\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        if tool.endswith(\\\"_subagent\\\"):\\n            tool = tool.replace(\\\"_subagent\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        if tool not in (\\\"\\\", \\\"unknown\\\", \\\"none\\\"):\\n            tags.add(tool)\\n    \\n    # Failure class (fourth part) - key failure mode\\n    if len(parts) > 3:\\n        fail = parts[3].lower()\\n        # Add as tag, but split if snake_case\\n        add_meaningful(fail, exclude_generic=True)\\n    \\n    # Root cause signature (fifth part) - extract keywords\\n    if len(parts) > 4:\\n        root = parts[4].lower()\\n        add_meaningful(root, exclude_generic=True)\\n    \\n    # Add contextual tags from prevention rule if we have too few\\n    rule = learning_entry.get('prevention_rule', '').lower()\\n    if rule and len(tags) < 4:\\n        # Extract key words from rule\\n        keywords = [\\\"batch\\\", \\\"split\\\", \\\"limit\\\", \\\"timeout\\\", \\\"handoff\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n                    \\\"reasoning\\\", \\\"mode\\\", \\\"sub-agent\\\", \\\"validator\\\", \\\"items\\\", \\\"count\\\"]\\n        for kw in keywords:\\n            if kw in rule:\\n                tags.add(kw)\\n    \\n    # Ensure we have at least 3 tags, but avoid generic filler\\n    # If still too few, add domain-specific fallbacks\\n    if len(tags) < 3:\\n        # Add from predefined contextual set based on domain\\n        domain = parts[0].lower() if parts else \\\"\\\"\\n        if domain == \\\"validation\\\":\\n            tags.update([\\\"batching\\\", \\\"timeout\\\", \\\"workload\\\"])\\n        elif domain == \\\"multi_agent\\\":\\n            tags.update([\\\"delegation\\\", \\\"handoff\\\", \\\"reporting\\\"])\\n        elif domain == \\\"model\\\":\\n            tags.update([\\\"api\\\", \\\"reasoning\\\", \\\"configuration\\\"])\\n        else:\\n            # Last resort: add from pattern key parts without filtering\\n            for p in parts[1:]:\\n                if p:\\n                    tags.add(p.lower().replace('_', '-'))\\n    \\n    # Keep only first 6, sorted\\n    return list(sorted(tags))[:6]\\n\\ndef parse_errors_md(path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Extract Pattern‑Keys from ERRORS.md entries.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n        content = f.read()\\n    \\n    pattern = r'### Pattern-Key:\\\\s*(.+?)\\\\n(.*?)(?=\\\\n### Pattern-Key:|\\\\Z)'\\n    matches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\\n    keys = []\\n    for pk_line, block in matches:\\n        pk = pk_line.strip().strip(':')\\n        data = {'pattern_key': pk}\\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in block.split('\\\\n') if l.strip()]\\n        for line in lines:\\n            if line.startswith('- **First Occurrence**:'):\\n                match = re.search(r'(\\\\d{4}-\\\\d{2}-\\\\d{2})', line)\\n                if match:\\n                    data['first_seen'] = match.group(1)\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Latest Occurrence**:'):\\n                match = re.search(r'(\\\\d{4}-\\\\d{2}-\\\\d{2})', line)\\n                if match:\\n                    data['last_seen'] = match.group(1)\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Count**:'):\\n                match = re.search(r'(\\\\d+)', line)\\n                if match:\\n                    data['count'] = int(match.group(1))\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Type**:'):\\n                data['type'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Severity**:'):\\n                data['severity'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n        data.setdefault('count', 1)\\n        data.setdefault('first_seen', 'unknown')\\n        data.setdefault('last_seen', 'unknown')\\n        data.setdefault('type', 'unknown')\\n        data.setdefault('severity', 'unknown')\\n        data['status'] = 'active'\\n        keys.append(data)\\n    return keys\\n\\ndef parse_learnings_md(path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Extract learning statements, prevention rules, and promotion status from LEARNINGS.md.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n        content = f.read()\\n    \\n    pattern = r'### Pattern-Key:\\\\s*(.+?)\\\\n(.*?)(?=\\\\n### Pattern-Key:|\\\\Z)'\\n    matches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\\n    learnings = {}\\n    for pk_line, block in matches:\\n        pk = pk_line.strip().strip(':')\\n        data = {'learning': '', 'prevention_rule': '', 'preflight': '', 'promoted_to': ''}\\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in block.split('\\\\n') if l.strip()]\\n        for line in lines:\\n            if line.startswith('- **Learning Statement**:'):\\n                data['learning'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Prevention Rule**:'):\\n                data['prevention_rule'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Preflight Checks**:'):\\n                data['preflight'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n            elif line.startswith('- **Promoted To**:'):\\n                data['promoted_to'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\\n        learnings[pk] = data\\n    return learnings\\n\\ndef extract_guardrails(agents_path, tools_path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Detect which Pattern‑Keys have guardrails in AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    promoted = set()\\n    def search_in_file(path, section_marker):\\n        try:\\n            with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n                content = f.read()\\n        except FileNotFoundError:\\n            return set()\\n        # Find the guardrail section\\n        # Match from section_marker to next ## or end of file\\n        pattern = rf'{re.escape(section_marker)}(.*?)(?=\\\\n## |\\\\Z)'\\n        match = re.search(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\\n        if not match:\\n            return set()\\n        section_text = match.group(1)\\n        # Look for Pattern‑Key lines (allow hyphen/dash and optional bold markers)\\n        # Matches **Pattern‑Key**: value or Pattern-Key: value\\n        pk_matches = re.findall(r'\\\\**Pattern[\\\\-‑]Key\\\\**:\\\\s*([^\\\\s]+)', section_text)\\n        return set(pk_matches)\\n    \\n    # AGENTS.md guardrail section\\n    promoted.update(search_in_file(agents_path, \\\"## Guardrails (Auto-learnings)\\\"))\\n    # TOOLS.md guardrail section\\n    promoted.update(search_in_file(tools_path, \\\"## Tool Guardrails\\\"))\\n    return promoted\\n\\ndef deduplicate_entries(errors_keys, learnings):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Merge duplicate Pattern‑Keys across sources.\\n    Returns a dict {pattern_key: merged_data}.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    merged = {}\\n    for k in errors_keys:\\n        pk = k['pattern_key']\\n        if pk not in merged:\\n            merged[pk] = {\\n                'pattern_key': pk,\\n                'count': k['count'],\\n                'first_seen': k['first_seen'],\\n                'last_seen': k['last_seen'],\\n                'type': k['type'],\\n                'severity': k['severity'],\\n                'status': k['status']\\n            }\\n        else:\\n            # Keep highest count\\n            if k['count'] > merged[pk]['count']:\\n                merged[pk]['count'] = k['count']\\n            # Keep newest last_seen (string comparison works for YYYY-MM-DD)\\n            if k['last_seen'] > merged[pk]['last_seen']:\\n                merged[pk]['last_seen'] = k['last_seen']\\n            # Prefer non‑unknown type/severity\\n            if k['type'] != 'unknown':\\n                merged[pk]['type'] = k['type']\\n            if k['severity'] != 'unknown':\\n                merged[pk]['severity'] = k['severity']\\n    # Add learning data\\n    for pk, data in learnings.items():\\n        if pk in merged:\\n            merged[pk]['learning'] = data['learning']\\n            merged[pk]['prevention_rule'] = data['prevention_rule']\\n            merged[pk]['preflight'] = data['preflight']\\n            merged[pk]['promoted_to'] = data['promoted_to']\\n        else:\\n            # Learning without error entry? Should not happen, but create stub.\\n            merged[pk] = {\\n                'pattern_key': pk,\\n                'count': 0,\\n                'first_seen': 'unknown',\\n                'last_seen': 'unknown',\\n                'type': 'unknown',\\n                'severity': 'unknown',\\n                'status': 'active',\\n                'learning': data['learning'],\\n                'prevention_rule': data['prevention_rule'],\\n                'preflight': data['preflight'],\\n                'promoted_to': data['promoted_to']\\n            }\\n    return merged\\n\\ndef generate_index(merged_entries, promoted_set, base_dir):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Create lightweight INDEX.md grouped by fixed domain sections.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    now = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\\n    # Group by domain section\\n    sections = {sec: [] for sec in DOMAIN_SECTIONS}\\n    for pk, data in sorted(merged_entries.items(), key=lambda x: x[0]):\\n        domain = classify_domain(pk)\\n        section = domain if domain in DOMAIN_SECTIONS else \\\"other\\\"\\n        tags = generate_tags(pk, data)\\n        rule = data.get('prevention_rule', '').strip()\\n        if not rule:\\n            rule = data.get('learning', '').strip()\\n            if rule:\\n                rule = rule[:120] + \\\"…\\\" if len(rule) > 120 else rule\\n        promoted = \\\"\\\"\\n        if pk in promoted_set:\\n            promoted = \\\"AGENTS.md\\\" if \\\"AGENTS.md\\\" in data.get('promoted_to', '') else \\\"TOOLS.md\\\"\\n        entry_lines = [\\n            f\\\"- Pattern-Key: {pk}\\\",\\n            f\\\"  Tags: {', '.join(tags)}\\\",\\n            f\\\"  Rule: {rule}\\\" if rule else \\\"\\\",\\n            f\\\"  Promoted: {promoted}\\\" if promoted else \\\"\\\"\\n        ]\\n        entry = \\\"\\\\n\\\".join([l for l in entry_lines if l])\\n        sections[section].append(entry)\\n    \\n    # Build content\\n    lines = [\\n        \\\"# INDEX.md – Lightweight Retrieval Index\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: \\\" + now + \\\"*\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"---\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\"\\n    ]\\n    for section in DOMAIN_SECTIONS:\\n        entries = sections[section]\\n        if not entries:\\n            continue\\n        lines.append(f\\\"## {section}\\\")\\n        lines.append(\\\"\\\")\\n        lines.extend(entries)\\n        lines.append(\\\"\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"---\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"*Sections: \\\" + \\\", \\\".join(DOMAIN_SECTIONS) + \\\"*\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"**Purpose**: Quick scanning of Pattern‑Keys, tags, rules, and promotion status.\\\")\\n    lines.append(\\\"For detailed analytics, see [REPORT.md](./REPORT.md).\\\")\\n    return \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(lines)\\n\\ndef generate_report(merged_entries, promoted_set, base_dir):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Create REPORT.md with analytics, tables, and trends.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    now = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\\n    total_incidents = sum(d['count'] for d in merged_entries.values())\\n    unique_pks = len(merged_entries)\\n    promoted_count = len(promoted_set)\\n    \\n    # Domain distribution\\n    domains = defaultdict(int)\\n    for pk in merged_entries:\\n        dom = classify_domain(pk)\\n        domains[dom] += 1\\n    \\n    # Severity distribution\\n    severities = defaultdict(int)\\n    for d in merged_entries.values():\\n        sev = d.get('severity', 'unknown')\\n        severities[sev] += 1\\n    \\n    # Type distribution\\n    types = defaultdict(int)\\n    for d in merged_entries.values():\\n        typ = d.get('type', 'unknown')\\n        types[typ] += 1\\n    \\n    # Pattern‑Key table rows\\n    table_rows = []\\n    for pk, data in sorted(merged_entries.items(), key=lambda x: x[0]):\\n        promoted = \\\"✅\\\" if pk in promoted_set else \\\"❌\\\"\\n        table_rows.append(\\n            f\\\"| `{pk}` | {data.get('type', '?')} | {data.get('severity', '?')} | \\\"\\n            f\\\"{data['count']} | {data.get('first_seen', '?')} | {data.get('last_seen', '?')} | \\\"\\n            f\\\"{promoted} |\\\"\\n        )\\n    \\n    content = f'''# REPORT.md – Learning‑Loop Analytics\\n\\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: {now}*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📊 Summary\\n\\n| Metric | Value |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| **Total incidents logged** | {total_incidents} |\\n| **Unique Pattern‑Keys** | {unique_pks} |\\n| **Pattern‑Keys with guardrails promoted** | {promoted_count} |\\n| **Promotion rate** | {promoted_count}/{unique_pks} ({promoted_count/unique_pks*100 if unique_pks else 0:.1f}%) |\\n| **Last refresh** | {now} |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔍 Pattern‑Key Table\\n\\n| Pattern‑Key | Type | Severity | Count | First Seen | Last Seen | Promoted |\\n|-------------|------|----------|-------|------------|-----------|----------|\\n{\\\"\\\\n\\\".join(table_rows)}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📈 Trend Analysis\\n\\n### Domain Distribution\\n{chr(10).join(f\\\"- **{dom}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\\\" for dom, cnt in sorted(domains.items()))}\\n\\n### Severity Distribution\\n{chr(10).join(f\\\"- **{sev}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\\\" for sev, cnt in sorted(severities.items()))}\\n\\n### Type Distribution\\n{chr(10).join(f\\\"- **{typ}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\\\" for typ, cnt in sorted(types.items()))}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🛡️ Promotion Statistics\\n\\n- **Promoted to AGENTS.md**: {sum(1 for pk in promoted_set if \\\"AGENTS.md\\\" in merged_entries.get(pk, {}).get('promoted_to', ''))}\\n- **Promoted to TOOLS.md**: {sum(1 for pk in promoted_set if \\\"TOOLS.md\\\" in merged_entries.get(pk, {}).get('promoted_to', ''))}\\n- **Not promoted**: {unique_pks - promoted_count}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📁 File Reference\\n\\n| File | Purpose | Last Updated |\\n|------|---------|--------------|\\n| [ERRORS.md](./ERRORS.md) | Deduplicated incident log with root‑cause analysis. | {now} |\\n| [LEARNINGS.md](./LEARNINGS.md) | Actionable learnings, prevention rules, preflight checks. | {now} |\\n| [FEATURE_REQUESTS.md](./FEATURE_REQUESTS.md) | Capability gaps identified from incidents. | {now} |\\n| [INDEX.md](./INDEX.md) | Lightweight retrieval index (this file’s companion). | {now} |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔄 Update Process\\n\\nThis report is regenerated each time `update_index.py` runs, usually after a learning‑loop execution.\\n\\n**Script location**: `{Path(__file__).relative_to(base_dir)}`\\n\\n**Manual refresh**:\\n```bash\\npython3 {Path(__file__).relative_to(base_dir)}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Maintained by**: main agent  \\n**Skill**: `error‑learning‑loop`'''\\n    return content\\n\\ndef append_incident_to_errors(\\n    errors_path,\\n    pattern_key,\\n    severity,\\n    source_skill,\\n    description,\\n    evidence,\\n    incident_type=None,\\n    symptoms=None,\\n    root_cause=None,\\n    fix_applied=None,\\n    tags=None\\n):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Append a new incident entry to ERRORS.md.\\n    If ERRORS.md does not exist, creates it with proper header.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    errors_path = Path(errors_path)\\n    now = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\\n    \\n    # Build entry lines\\n    lines = [\\n        f\\\"### Pattern-Key: {pattern_key}\\\",\\n        f\\\"- **First Occurrence**: {now} (from {source_skill})\\\",\\n        f\\\"- **Latest Occurrence**: {now}\\\",\\n        f\\\"- **Count**: 1\\\",\\n        f\\\"- **Type**: {incident_type if incident_type else 'INCIDENT'}\\\",\\n        f\\\"- **Severity**: {severity}\\\",\\n    ]\\n    if symptoms:\\n        lines.append(\\\"- **Symptoms**:\\\")\\n        for symptom in symptoms if isinstance(symptoms, list) else [symptoms]:\\n            lines.append(f\\\"  - {symptom}\\\")\\n    else:\\n        lines.append(\\\"- **Symptoms**:\\\")\\n        lines.append(f\\\"  - {description}\\\")\\n    \\n    lines.append(f\\\"- **Evidence**: \\\\\\\"{evidence}\\\\\\\"\\\")\\n    \\n    if root_cause:\\n        lines.append(f\\\"- **Root Cause Hypothesis**: {root_cause}\\\")\\n    else:\\n        lines.append(f\\\"- **Root Cause Hypothesis**: {description}\\\")\\n    \\n    if fix_applied:\\n        lines.append(f\\\"- **Fix Applied**: {fix_applied}\\\")\\n    else:\\n        lines.append(\\\"- **Fix Applied**: None\\\")\\n    \\n    if tags:\\n        tag_str = \\\", \\\".join(tags) if isinstance(tags, list) else tags\\n        lines.append(f\\\"- **Tags**: {tag_str}\\\")\\n    else:\\n        lines.append(f\\\"- **Tags**: skill={source_skill}\\\")\\n    \\n    lines.append(\\\"\\\")  # blank line before next entry\\n    \\n    entry_text = \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(lines)\\n    \\n    # Read current content\\n    if errors_path.exists():\\n        content = errors_path.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\\n        # Find where \\\"## Entries\\\" section ends, or append before EOF\\n        entries_marker = \\\"## Entries\\\"\\n        if entries_marker in content:\\n            # Insert after the last entry before next ### Pattern-Key or end of section\\n            # We'll simply append after the last entry, before the end of file\\n            # Simpler: find the position of the last \\\"### Pattern-Key:\\\" and insert after its block\\n            # But we can just append at the end of the file, before any trailing newlines\\n            # Ensure there is a blank line before new entry\\n            if content.endswith('\\\\n\\\\n'):\\n                pass\\n            elif content.endswith('\\\\n'):\\n                content += '\\\\n'\\n            else:\\n                content += '\\\\n\\\\n'\\n            content += entry_text\\n        else:\\n            # Create Entries section\\n            if content.endswith('\\\\n'):\\n                content += '\\\\n'\\n            else:\\n                content += '\\\\n\\\\n'\\n            content += \\\"## Entries\\\\n\\\\n\\\" + entry_text\\n    else:\\n        # Create new file with header\\n        header = f\\\"\\\"\\\"# ERRORS.md – Deduplicated Incident Log\\n\\n*Generated by error-learning-loop. Updated: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')}*\\n\\n## Pattern-Key Index\\n| Pattern-Key | Count | First Seen | Last Seen | Status |\\n|-------------|-------|------------|-----------|--------|\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Entries\\n\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        content = header + entry_text\\n    \\n    errors_path.write_text(content, encoding='utf-8')\\n    return True\\n\\ndef trigger_learning_loop(base_dir=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Trigger the learning loop by running update_index.py.\\n    Returns True on success.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if base_dir is None:\\n        base_dir = Path.cwd()\\n    script_path = Path(__file__).parent / 'update_index.py'\\n    import subprocess\\n    result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, str(script_path), str(base_dir)], \\n                            capture_output=True, text=True)\\n    if result.returncode != 0:\\n        print(f\\\"Error running update_index: {result.stderr}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n        return False\\n    return True\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772811834664\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now we need to create emit_incident.py that uses common.append_incident_to_errors and optionally triggers learning loop. We'll also add a command line interface. Let's create it:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_yBaftvcPPVeVHSvrmYWfymaJ\",\n          \"name\": \"write\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/emit_incident.py\",\n            \"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nemit_incident.py – Unified incident emitter for the error-learning-loop.\\nCall this script from other skills to log incidents and optionally trigger learning.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport sys\\nimport argparse\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\n# Add the scripts directory to path to import common\\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))\\nfrom common import append_incident_to_errors, trigger_learning_loop\\n\\ndef emit_incident(\\n    pattern_key,\\n    severity,\\n    source_skill,\\n    description,\\n    evidence,\\n    incident_type=None,\\n    symptoms=None,\\n    root_cause=None,\\n    fix_applied=None,\\n    tags=None,\\n    trigger_learning=True,\\n    base_dir=None\\n):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Emit an incident to ERRORS.md and optionally trigger learning loop.\\n    \\n    Args:\\n        pattern_key (str): Pattern‑Key in format domain|type|tool|failure_class|root_cause_signature\\n        severity (str): Severity level (e.g., S1, S2, S3, S4)\\n        source_skill (str): Name of skill that emitted this incident\\n        description (str): Brief description of the incident\\n        evidence (str): Concrete evidence (1 line, no secrets)\\n        incident_type (str): Optional incident type (e.g., ERROR, NEAR_MISS, TOOL_FAILURE)\\n        symptoms (list or str): Optional list of symptoms or single string\\n        root_cause (str): Optional root cause hypothesis\\n        fix_applied (str): Optional fix applied\\n        tags (list or str): Optional tags for categorization\\n        trigger_learning (bool): Whether to run learning loop after emitting (default True)\\n        base_dir (Path): Base workspace directory (defaults to parent of .learnings)\\n    \\n    Returns:\\n        bool: True on success\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if base_dir is None:\\n        # Guess workspace root: go up from .learnings directory\\n        learnings = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace' / '.learnings'\\n        if learnings.exists():\\n            base_dir = learnings.parent\\n        else:\\n            base_dir = Path.cwd()\\n    \\n    errors_path = base_dir / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\\n    \\n    # Ensure .learnings directory exists\\n    errors_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n    \\n    # Append incident\\n    success = append_incident_to_errors(\\n        errors_path,\\n        pattern_key,\\n        severity,\\n        source_skill,\\n        description,\\n        evidence,\\n        incident_type=incident_type,\\n        symptoms=symptoms,\\n        root_cause=root_cause,\\n        fix_applied=fix_applied,\\n        tags=tags\\n    )\\n    \\n    if not success:\\n        print(\\\"Failed to append incident\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n        return False\\n    \\n    print(f\\\"Incident logged: {pattern_key}\\\")\\n    \\n    # Optionally trigger learning loop\\n    if trigger_learning:\\n        print(\\\"Triggering learning loop...\\\")\\n        if not trigger_learning_loop(base_dir):\\n            print(\\\"Learning loop trigger failed\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n            # Non‑fatal\\n    return True\\n\\ndef main():\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n        description=\\\"Emit an incident to the error‑learning‑loop system.\\\"\\n    )\\n    parser.add_argument('pattern_key', help='Pattern‑Key (domain|type|tool|failure_class|root_cause)')\\n    parser.add_argument('severity', help='Severity (S1–S4)')\\n    parser.add_argument('source_skill', help='Source skill name')\\n    parser.add_argument('description', help='Brief description')\\n    parser.add_argument('evidence', help='Concrete evidence (1 line)')\\n    parser.add_argument('--type', dest='incident_type', default='INCIDENT', \\n                        help='Incident type (ERROR, NEAR_MISS, etc.)')\\n    parser.add_argument('--symptoms', nargs='+', help='List of symptoms')\\n    parser.add_argument('--root-cause', dest='root_cause', help='Root cause hypothesis')\\n    parser.add_argument('--fix', dest='fix_applied', help='Fix applied')\\n    parser.add_argument('--tags', nargs='+', help='Tags (skill=..., agent=...)')\\n    parser.add_argument('--no-trigger', action='store_true', \\n                        help='Do not trigger learning loop after emitting')\\n    parser.add_argument('--base-dir', help='Workspace base directory (default auto‑detect)')\\n    \\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n    \\n    base_dir = Path(args.base_dir) if args.base_dir else None\\n    \\n    return emit_incident(\\n        pattern_key=args.pattern_key,\\n        severity=args.severity,\\n        source_skill=args.source_skill,\\n        description=args.description,\\n        evidence=args.evidence,\\n        incident_type=args.incident_type,\\n        symptoms=args.symptoms,\\n        root_cause=args.root_cause,\\n        fix_applied=args.fix_applied,\\n        tags=args.tags,\\n        trigger_learning=not args.no_trigger,\\n        base_dir=base_dir\\n    )\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    success = main()\\n    sys.exit(0 if success else 1)\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772812076551\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": true,\n  \"bytes\": 40581\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:a98d0427-ea71-40e5-96fc-d7350d0bce09","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: ## Task: Hardening and Automation Upgrade for `error-learning-loop` skill\n\nYou are a specialized sub-agent tasked with enhancing the existing skill located at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop`. The goal is to make the learning system **fully autonomous**, reducing the need for manual intervention when processing incidents.\n\nYou must implement a **dual execution strategy**:\n1. Event‑Driven Learning (Primary)\n2. Scheduled Reconciliation (Backup via Cron)\n\nBoth must coexist to guarantee system reliability.\n\n## Current Skill Structure\n- SKILL.md defines manual and wrap-up modes.\n- Scripts directory currently contains only `update_index.py`.\n- Learning store at `~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/` includes ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, REPORT.md, FEATURE_REQUESTS.md.\n\n## Objective\nEnsure the `error-learning-loop` can:\n- Automatically capture incidents from all skills\n- Process incidents into Pattern‑Keys\n- Deduplicate semantically\n- Promote guardrails when patterns repeat\n- Update INDEX.md and REPORT.md automatically\n- Detect and process incidents that were missed by triggers\n\n## Architecture Upgrade\nImplement a **two‑layer automation model**:\n\n### Layer 1 — Event‑Driven Processing (Primary)\nThe system must trigger learning automatically whenever any of the following occurs:\n- A sub‑agent finishes execution\n- A Handoff Report contains incidents\n- agent-watchdog detects stall or deadlock\n- A skill writes to `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- A complex task finishes execution\n\nRequired flow:\nemit_incident()\n→ append .learnings/ERRORS.md\n→ trigger error-learning-loop\n→ rebuild INDEX.md\n→ update REPORT.md\n\nAll skills must call a **unified incident interface**.\n\nExample interface:\nemit_incident(\n  pattern_key,\n  severity,\n  source_skill,\n  description,\n  evidence\n)\n\nYou need to create:\n- `scripts/emit_incident.py` – unified incident emitter that writes to ERRORS.md and triggers learning loop (if event-driven mode enabled).\n- `scripts/event_trigger_listener.py` – a script that can be invoked by other skills to register incidents and trigger processing. It should also handle automatic invocation when Handoff Reports are detected (maybe via a wrapper function). For simplicity, we can make emit_incident also call the learning loop directly (by importing existing functions from update_index.py). However, we need to avoid circular imports. Consider refactoring common logic into a shared module.\n\n### Layer 2 — Scheduled Reconciliation (Cron Backup)\nA scheduled job must run daily to ensure **no incidents remain unprocessed**.\n\nRecommended schedule: Monday–Friday at 1:30 PM Panama Time (America/Panama).\n\nThe cron task must:\n1. Scan `.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n2. Detect incidents not yet processed (i.e., those missing from INDEX.md)\n3. Detect Pattern‑Keys missing from INDEX.md\n4. Rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md\n5. Promote new guardrails if thresholds are met\n6. Generate a reconciliation summary\n\nThe cron job must **never overwrite previous learning history**.\n\nCreate:\n- `scripts/reconcile_incidents.py` – scans ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, INDEX.md, identifies unprocessed incidents, and runs the learning loop on them.\n- `scripts/cron_reconciliation_runner.py` – wrapper that sets up environment and calls reconcile_incidents.py; also logs start/end times.\n\n## Incident Coverage Expansion\nExtend Pattern‑Key coverage for common system issues (add to pattern key mapping):\n- Model Stalls: `runtime|STALL|model|no_response`\n- Deadlocks: `runtime|DEADLOCK|multi_agent|dependency_cycle`\n- FIT/GAP failures: `fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify`\n- Token overflow: `tokens|OVERFLOW|context_window|exceeded`\n- Checkpoint failures: `recovery|FAILURE|checkpoint_missing`\n- Security violations: `security|FLS_MISSING|apex`\n\nEnsure these patterns are recognized during semantic deduplication.\n\n## Guardrail Promotio\n…(truncated)…"}],"timestamp":1772811771474},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll start by examining the current skill structure and the existing update_index.py to understand the deduplication logic. First, read the skill's SKILL.md to get the current documentation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XykjKTH2eKXRYHRYZolfNyso","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md"}}],"api