{"type":"message","id":"6fc24887","parentId":"a87fcefe","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:00:04.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the skill mentions the script but not a command. However the skill is user-invocable with command-dispatch: model. That means the agent decides what to do. We can add a note in AGENTS.md that when receiving \"error-learning-loop reconcile\", run the cron reconciliation script. But that's a manual addition.\n\nBetter to add a cron job that directly executes the Python script using the system's cron (crontab). That's independent of the agent and ensures it runs even if the agent is not active. Since we have a watchdog that monitors agents, but cron reconciliation is a backup layer. It's okay to be system-level.\n\nLet's add a crontab entry for user openclaw. We'll need to ensure the script is executable. Let's check permissions. Let's make the script executable. Let's also test it with a dry run.\n\nFirst, make the script executable:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_pDVtWLuSN9YV0mkcOCfvV8ph","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"chmod +x ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/cron_reconciliation_runner.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":221,"output":438,"cacheRead":68160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68819,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772812792147}}
