{"type":"message","id":"62f1097e","parentId":"232985d8","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:02:24.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect. Now we have the scheduled reconciliation layer.\n\nNow we need to ensure event-driven layer works. That requires other skills to call emit_incident. We need to integrate with watchdog. The watchdog currently has its own incident emission that writes to ERRORS.md and triggers learning loop. That's good. However it uses its own append_to_errors method. We should modify watchdog to use the new emit_incident script for consistency. That's an integration task. But the sub-agent might be working on that. Let's see if the sub-agent has updated watchdog. Let's check watchdog_orchestrator.py for recent changes (maybe they added import). Let's search for \"emit_incident\". Let's grep.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6g1JsCocK2o6T9RbYab2Mg2O","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n emit_incident ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":49124,"output":369,"cacheRead":19456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772812921038}}
