{"type":"message","id":"b05d4405","parentId":"9672e29d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:02:45.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So watchdog has its own emit_incident method. It currently writes to ERRORS.md and triggers update_index.py (as we saw). That's fine; it's already integrated with learning loop. However we need to ensure it uses the new Pattern‑Key expansions (model stalls, deadlocks, etc). Let's examine that method. Let's read lines around 96. Let's read the method. Let's view that part of the file. Let's use read with offset. Let's first find the exact line numbers. Let's get more context:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_U0hJZzneNZA8S4Wo1EkwvqUP","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py","offset":90,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":45221,"output":327,"cacheRead":19584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65132,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772812944773}}
{"type":"message","id":"d927137b","parentId":"b05d4405","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:02:45.630Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_U0hJZzneNZA8S4Wo1EkwvqUP","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            pass\n        elif action == 'relaunch_agent':\n            # Close session and relaunch\n            pass\n        return action\n    \n    def emit_incident(self, session, stall_duration, recovery_level, success):\n        \"\"\"Generate incident and append to ERRORS.md.\"\"\"\n        incident = generate_incident(\n            session.model,\n            stall_duration,\n            recovery_level,\n            success\n        )\n        # Add extra telemetry fields\n        incident['task_type'] = session.task_description\n        incident['items_count'] = getattr(session, 'items_count', 0)\n        incident['runtime_type'] = session.runtime_type\n        \n        # Append to ERRORS.md (will automatically trigger learning loop)\n        self.append_to_errors(incident, trigger_learning=True)\n        \n        return incident\n    \n    def append_to_errors(self, incident, trigger_learning=True):\n        \"\"\"Append incident to ERRORS.md following the pattern-key format.\n        If trigger_learning=True, also trigger the learning loop.\"\"\"\n        if not ERRORS_PATH.exists():\n            return\n        \n        # Rate limiting check\n        pattern_key = incident.get('pattern_key', 'unknown')\n        if not self._rate_limit_check(pattern_key):\n            print(f\"[Watchdog] Rate limit hit for {pattern_key} — skipped append.\")\n            # Still allow index rebuild if triggered (but debounced)\n            if trigger_learning:\n                result = self.trigger_learning_loop(incident)\n                if result['triggered']:\n                    print(f\"[Watchdog] Learning loop triggered via {result['method']} (rate-limited incident)\")\n            return\n        \n        with open(ERRORS_PATH, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            f.write(f\"\\n### Pattern-Key: {pattern_key}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **First Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Latest Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Count**: 1\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Type**: stall\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Severity**: S2\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Model**: {incident.get('model', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Stall Duration**: {incident.get('stall_duration', 0)} seconds\\n\")\n\n[279 more lines in file. Use offset=140 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772812965620}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c6f7cc1","parentId":"d927137b","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:02:59.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looks like watchdog uses its own append_to_errors but triggers learning loop via trigger_learning_loop method which calls update_index.py. That's fine; it's already integrated with learning loop. However we need to ensure the pattern key uses the new expanded set. Let's see what generate_incident returns (from watchdog_learning_adapter). We already saw it returns pattern_key \"model|STALL|{model}|no_response|runtime_stuck\". That's good, matches the new pattern.\n\nNow we need to ensure that other skills can call emit_incident script. We'll need to update SKILL.md for error-learning-loop to include usage instructions for other skills. That's a documentation update. The sub-agent might have already updated SKILL.md. Let's check if SKILL.md has been updated recently. Let's look at the end of the file for new sections. Let's read the last part.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tIm1BxBgUnck2cFgGKQvERgb","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md","offset":150}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":783,"output":451,"cacheRead":64768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66002,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772812965630}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef4a283e","parentId":"7c6f7cc1","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:02:59.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_tIm1BxBgUnck2cFgGKQvERgb","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern hint: <optional, 1 line>\nPrevention rule: <optional, 1 line>\nFiles touched: <list or \"none\">\nNext action: <1 line>\n\n### Rules for sub-agents\n- Do NOT include secrets/tokens/credentials.\n- Keep evidence brief and concrete.\n- If there were no incidents: set Outcome=success and Incidents: none.\n\n## Core Concept: Semantic Dedupe\nTraditional dedupe compares exact strings.\nSemantic dedupe groups incidents by **meaning** into stable Pattern-Keys.\n\nExample (all same semantic class):\n- \"rg command not found\"\n- \"ripgrep missing\"\n- \"bash failed because rg not installed\"\n→ Pattern-Key: tools|TOOL_FAILURE|bash|missing_binary|binary_not_in_path\n\n## Pattern-Key\nFormat:\n<domain>|<type>|<tool>|<failure_class>|<root_cause_signature>\n\n## Hard Safety Rules (non-negotiable)\n1) Only read/write inside the current workspace and {baseDir}. Never edit outside.\n2) Never store secrets, tokens, passwords, keys, or private identifiers in learnings/logs.\n3) Do NOT install dependencies; do NOT auto-refactor code; do NOT change global OpenClaw config.\n4) Session/history access (if available) is allowed only when invoked and only for relevant sessions.\n5) Prefer minimal, auditable edits: small diffs, clear headings, and dated entries.\n6) If unsure whether something is sensitive: redact it.\n\n## Mitigations (to prevent common failure modes)\n### M1 — Prevent overfitting (bad generalizations)\nPromote a learning to AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md only if it is generalizable AND:\n- repeated Pattern-Key occurrences >= 2, OR\n- Severity is S1/S2 structural issue.\n\nOtherwise keep it in .learnings only.\n\n### M2 — Prevent logging noise\nKeep entries concise:\n- Symptoms: max 6 bullets\n- Root Cause: max 4 bullets\n- 1 learning sentence\n- 1 prevention rule\n- Preflight: 2–6 checks max\n\n### M3 — Prevent sensitive-data leakage\nBefore writing:\n- redact tokens/keys/passwords\n- replace emails/phones with placeholders\n- avoid customer names unless explicitly required\n\n### M4 — Prevent uncontrolled scope creep\nIf the fix requires new capability:\n- log as FEATURE_REQUEST\n- do not implement automatically\n\n## Inputs\nFrom current context:\n- Task goal (1–2 sentences)\n- Evidence: tool outputs, user corrections\n- Tags (mandatory):\n  - agent=<name>\n  - session=<id>\n  - task=<short>\n\nFrom sub-agents (required):\n- Handoff Report blocks (as provided in chat)\n\nOptional (only for dedupe confirmation):\n- Minimal relevant session history snippets (if tools exist)\n\n## Outputs\nAlways update at least one:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n\nSometimes:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n- Workspace patches (minimal):\n  - `<workspace>/AGENTS.md`\n  - `<workspace>/TOOLS.md`\n\n**New mandatory output** (added in this version):\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md` – consolidated index of Pattern‑Keys, guardrails, and trends. Must be updated and deduplicated after every learning‑loop run.\n\n## Step-by-step instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Ensure learning store exists\nCreate if missing:\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n- `<workspace>/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n\n### Step 1 — Detect incidents (wrap-up gate)\nIf running wrap-up:\n- Confirm at least one incident occurred (from main execution or sub-agent handoff).\n- If none: STOP. No logging.\n\n*Note*: In **event‑driven mode**, incidents are detected automatically via `emit_incident()` calls from other skills (e.g., `agent‑watchdog`, sub‑agent handoff reports). The wrap‑up gate is bypassed and learning loop is triggered immediately.\n\n### Step 2 — Collect evidence (main + sub-agents)\nFrom the main task:\n- what we attempted\n- what happened\n- root cause hypothesis\n- what fixed it\n\nFrom sub-agents:\n- parse each Handoff Report\n- extract Outcome + each Incident line\n- discard/redact anything sensitive\n\n### Step 3 — Generate Semantic Pattern-Key\nFor each incident:\n- normalize into a stable Pattern-Key using:\n  domain + type + tool (if any) + failure_class + root_cause_signature\n\n### Step 4 — Semantic Deduplication\nCompare against existing Pattern-Keys in:\n- .learnings/ERRORS.md\n- .learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n\nIf a semantically matching Pattern-Key exists:\n- increment Count\n- update Last Seen\n- append an Occurrence entry\n\nElse:\n- create a new entry\n\n### Step 5 — Extract Learning\nFor each (new or repeated) Pattern-Key:\n- 1 learning statement\n- 1 prevention rule\n- optional preflight checklist (tools-related only)\n\n### Step 6 — Promotion\nApply Mitigation M1.\nPromote:\n- workflow/coordination guardrails → AGENTS.md (\"## Guardrails (Auto-learnings)\")\n- tool-specific guardrails → TOOLS.md (\"## Tool Guardrails\")\n\nEdits must include:\n- date\n- Pattern-Key\n- rule (+ preflight if any)\n\n### Step 7 — Close\nAdd an applied note:\nApplied: yes/no\nPromoted to: AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none\nNext time: expected behavior\n\n### Step 8 — Update Learning Retrieval Index\n\n**Purpose**:\nMaintain a lightweight retrieval index so the agent can quickly find relevant Pattern‑Keys without scanning full logs.\n\n**Actions**:\n\n1. Read:\n   - `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n   - `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`\n\n2. Extract all Pattern‑Keys and derive:\n   - domain\n   - tags (3–6)\n   - rule (one line)\n   - promoted_to (AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none)\n\n3. Read:\n   - `AGENTS.md`\n   - `TOOLS.md`\n   to detect promoted guardrails.\n\n4. Rebuild `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md` from scratch with fixed domain sections.\n\n5. Deduplicate Pattern‑Keys globally.\n\n6. Ensure each entry contains at most 3–4 short lines.\n\n7. Write analytics and trend information to `<workspace>/.learnings/REPORT.md`.\n\n### Step 9 – Automated Reconciliation (Cron Backup)\nA scheduled job (`cron_reconciliation_runner.py`) runs daily (Mon–Fri, 1:30 PM Panama Time) to ensure no incidents remain unprocessed.\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Scan `.learnings/ERRORS.md` for incidents missing from `INDEX.md`.\n2. Scan `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` for missing learnings.\n3. Detect repeated incidents (count ≥2) without guardrails.\n4. Detect high‑severity incidents (S1/S2) without guardrails.\n5. If any gaps are found, trigger the learning loop (`update_index.py`).\n6. Log reconciliation summary to `.learnings/reconciliation.log`.\n\n**Note**: The cron job never overwrites previous learning history; it only adds missing entries.\n\n## Example usage\nManual:\n\"Run the learning loop using the sub-agent handoff reports from this task.\"\nWrap-up:\nIf incidents occurred, run Steps 2–8; otherwise skip.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772812979533}}
{"type":"message","id":"0cccb188","parentId":"ef4a283e","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:03:16.973Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The SKILL.md has been updated! It now includes sections about event-driven mode and cron backup. That's great. The sub-agent has already updated the skill documentation. So the automation upgrade is largely complete. We need to ensure the event-driven mode is operational: we need to test emit_incident script and ensure other skills (like watchdog) can call it. We'll also need to update watchdog to use the new emit_incident script (maybe optional). But watchdog already has its own method that writes to ERRORS.md and triggers learning loop. That's fine; we can keep it as is. However we should ensure it uses the same pattern key mapping.\n\nLet's test emit_incident script with a sample incident to see if it triggers learning loop. We'll run it with a dummy pattern key. Let's do that now. We'll use a pattern key \"test|DUPLICATE|test|test|test\" which already exists maybe. We'll set severity S4, source_skill \"test\", description \"test incident\", evidence \"test\". We'll run with --no-trigger to avoid duplicate learning loop. Let's do that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OBvNUJTjchbbb4Em2yijzEQe","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && python3 skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/emit_incident.py test\\|DUPLICATE\\|test\\|test\\|test S4 test \"test incident\" \"test\" --no-trigger 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1949,"output":574,"cacheRead":65536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68059,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772812979552}}
