{"type":"message","id":"c0fd2946","parentId":"fc78b591","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:09:46.434Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_n9uZnX1QZbEJPaPPIn1GEkeQ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            f.write(f\"- **Recovery Level**: {incident.get('recovery_level', 0)}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Success**: {incident.get('success', False)}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Runtime Type**: {incident.get('runtime_type', 'subagent')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Task Type**: {incident.get('task_type', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Items Count**: {incident.get('items_count', 0)}\\n\")\n            f.write(\"\\n\")\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Incident appended to {ERRORS_PATH}\")\n        \n        # Trigger learning loop unless explicitly disabled\n        if trigger_learning:\n            result = self.trigger_learning_loop(incident)\n            if result['triggered']:\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Learning loop triggered via {result['method']}\")\n            else:\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Learning loop NOT triggered: {result.get('error', 'unknown')}\")\n    \n    def trigger_learning_loop(self, incident):\n        \"\"\"Invoke the error-learning-loop skill or fallback to index rebuild.\"\"\"\n        result = {\n            'triggered': False,\n            'method': None,\n            'error': None\n        }\n        \n        # Try to spawn the error-learning-loop skill via OpenClaw sessions_spawn\n        # (This is the preferred method but may not be available in all contexts)\n        skill_invoked = self._try_invoke_learning_skill(incident)\n        if skill_invoked:\n            result['triggered'] = True\n            result['method'] = 'skill'\n            print(f\"[Watchdog] Successfully invoked error-learning-loop skill\")\n            return result\n        \n        # Fallback: rebuild index directly\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Skill invocation not available, using fallback index rebuild\")\n        fallback_success = self._rebuild_index_fallback()\n        if fallback_success:\n            result['triggered'] = True\n            result['method'] = 'fallback'\n        else:\n            result['error'] = 'Fallback index rebuild failed'\n        \n        return result\n    \n    def _try_invoke_learning_skill(self, incident):\n        \"\"\"Attempt to spawn error-learning-loop skill via OpenClaw sessions_spawn.\"\"\"\n        # This is a placeholder for integration with OpenClaw's sessions_spawn API.\n        # In a production deployment, this would call sessions_spawn with runtime=\"subagent\".\n        # For now, we return False to indicate skill invocation is not available.\n        return False\n    \n    def _rebuild_index_fallback(self):\n        \"\"\"Run update_index.py to rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md with debouncing.\"\"\"\n        with self.rebuild_lock:\n            now = datetime.utcnow()\n            if (self.last_index_rebuild is not None and \n                (now - self.last_index_rebuild).total_seconds() < REBUILD_DEBOUNCE_SECONDS):\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Index rebuild debounced (last rebuild: {self.last_index_rebuild})\")\n                return True  # Consider debounced as success (no need to rebuild again)\n            \n            if not UPDATE_INDEX_SCRIPT.exists():\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] ERROR: update_index.py not found at {UPDATE_INDEX_SCRIPT}\")\n                return False\n            \n            try:\n                cmd = [sys.executable, str(UPDATE_INDEX_SCRIPT), str(WORKSPACE)]\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Executing: {' '.join(cmd)}\")\n                result = subprocess.run(\n                    cmd,\n                    capture_output=True,\n                    text=True,\n                    timeout=30\n                )\n                if result.returncode == 0:\n                    self.last_index_rebuild = now\n                    print(f\"[Watchdog] Index rebuild successful: {result.stdout.strip()}\")\n                    return True\n                else:\n                    print(f\"[Watchdog] Index rebuild failed (exit {result.returncode}): {result.stderr}\")\n                    return False\n            except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Index rebuild timed out after 30 seconds\")\n                return False\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"[Watchdog] Index rebuild error: {e}\")\n                return False\n    \n    # Deadlock detection methods\n    def add_dependency(self, agent_id, waiting_for_agent_id):\n        \"\"\"Record that agent_id is waiting for waiting_for_agent_id.\"\"\"\n        self.agent_graph[agent_id] = waiting_for_agent_id\n    \n    def detect_deadlock(self):\n        \"\"\"Check dependency graph for cycles.\"\"\"\n        visited = set()\n        for agent in self.agent_graph:\n            if agent not in visited:\n                cycle = self._find_cycle(agent, [], visited)\n                if cycle:\n                    return cycle\n\n[179 more lines in file. Use offset=240 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772813386418}}
{"type":"message","id":"8201e3c5","parentId":"c0fd2946","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:10:21.195Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Vemos que el watchdog ya tiene su propia función append_to_errors que escribe directamente a ERRORS.md y luego llama a trigger_learning_loop que intenta invocar el skill error-learning-loop o ejecuta update_index.py. Pero ahora queremos que use emit_incident.py, que a su vez escribe en ERRORS.md y puede activar el learning loop. Podemos modificar append_to_errors para que en lugar de escribir directamente, llame a emit_incident.py (o importe la función). Sin embargo, emit_incident ya está diseñado para ser llamado desde otros skills. Debemos actualizar el watchdog para que use emit_incident.\n\nPrimero necesito verificar la ruta de emit_incident.py relativa al workspace. La ruta es ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/emit_incident.py. Podemos importar desde ahí o ejecutar subprocess.\n\nAhora, para cada skill, debo crear un sub-agente que:\n\n1. Identifique los puntos donde se emiten errores/incidentes.\n2. Modifique el código para usar emit_incident (ya sea importando la función o llamando al script).\n3. Asegure que no se rompa la funcionalidad existente.\n4. Pruebe la integración.\n\nTambién necesito monitorear el progreso de cada sub-agente y balancear la carga. Puedo crear un sub-agente por skill, pero puedo agrupar algunos para reducir la sobrecarga. Sin embargo, el usuario dijo \"repartelos a los Agentes independientes\". Asumiré que quiere un agente por skill.\n\nVoy a crear sesiones de sub-agente para: agent-watchdog, salesforce-architect, salesforce-code-auditor, workspace-janitor, long-prompt-orchestrator. Son 5. Los lanzaré en secuencia, pero puedo lanzarlos todos a la vez y monitorear. Necesito registrar cada uno con el watchdog para monitoreo de stalls.\n\nPrimero, necesito obtener el session_id y run_id después de spawn. Luego registrar con watchdog.\n\nVoy a escribir un script de registro de watchdog, pero puedo usar el script existente register_watchdog.py que ya creé. Lo modificaré para registrar múltiples sesiones.\n\nPero primero, voy a lanzar el sub-agente para agent-watchdog. Crearé una tarea específica.\n\nAntes de eso, necesito examinar cada skill para ver si ya tienen algún mecanismo de error reporting. Revisar salesforce-architect, salesforce-code-auditor, workspace-janitor, long-prompt-orchestrator.\n\nVoy a leer sus SKILL.md para ver si mencionan incidentes. Pero mejor buscar archivos .py en sus scripts. Usar find.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uP6lqcIZgbUjz97NoSSFWcN7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect -name \"*.py\" -type f"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":19097,"output":1301,"cacheRead":49600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69998,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772813386435}}
