{"type":"message","id":"80c6f079","parentId":"539d9e25","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:11:03.187Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_tiHRPN8e414VOktGykN6DnxK","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    return matched\n\ndef emit_incident(pattern_key, symptom, evidence='', severity='S2'):\n    \"\"\"\n    Append an incident to workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md.\n    \"\"\"\n    errors_file = WORKSPACE_ROOT / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\n    ensure_dir(errors_file.parent)\n    timestamp = subprocess.run(['date', '-Iseconds'], capture_output=True, text=True).stdout.strip()\n    session_id = os.environ.get('SESSION_ID', 'unknown')\n    entry = f\"\"\"\n## {timestamp} | session:{session_id}\n- Pattern: `{pattern_key}`\n- Symptom: {symptom}\n- Evidence: {evidence}\n- Severity: {severity}\n\"\"\"\n    with open(errors_file, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(entry)\n    logger.warning('Incident emitted: %s', pattern_key)\n    # Trigger learning loop fallback (placeholder)\n    # In production, call the error-learning-loop skill.\n    logger.info('Learning loop fallback triggered (placeholder).')\n\ndef validate_inputs(inputs):\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate mandatory inputs for Stage 0.\n    Returns list of missing fields.\n    \"\"\"\n    mandatory = [\n\n[18 more lines in file. Use offset=130 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772813463171}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0bc0d98","parentId":"80c6f079","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:12:19.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Entonces salesforce-architect ya tiene su propia función emit_incident que escribe en ERRORS.md con un formato diferente al nuevo formato. Necesitamos actualizarla para usar el nuevo emit_incident.py (el unificado). Similar para salesforce-code-auditor y otros.\n\nAhora necesito crear sub-agentes que hagan estas actualizaciones. Voy a escribir instrucciones claras.\n\nPrimero, para agent-watchdog. Voy a spawnear un sub-agente. Usaré sessions_spawn con runtime subagent, agentId main. La tarea será actualizar el script watchdog_orchestrator.py para usar emit_incident.py.\n\nPero también debemos considerar que el watchdog ya tiene trigger_learning_loop que intenta invocar el skill. Podríamos dejar eso como está, pero debemos cambiar append_to_errors para que use emit_incident. Sin embargo, emit_incident ya incluye trigger learning loop. Para evitar duplicación, podemos modificar append_to_errors para que llame a emit_incident con trigger_learning=True, y eliminar la llamada a trigger_learning_loop (o mantenerla como fallback). Pero debemos mantener compatibilidad.\n\nVoy a crear una tarea específica para cada skill.\n\nPrimero, crearé un sub-agente para agent-watchdog. Luego otro para salesforce-architect. Luego otro para salesforce-code-auditor. Luego otro para workspace-janitor. Luego otro para long-prompt-orchestrator. Eso son 5 sub-agentes. Los lanzaré uno tras otro, pero puedo lanzarlos en paralelo? sessions_spawn puede ejecutar en segundo plano. Puedo lanzarlos todos y luego monitorear con sessions_list.\n\nNecesito registrar cada uno con watchdog. Crearé un script de registro simple.\n\nPrimero, lanzar sub-agente para agent-watchdog. Voy a preparar la tarea.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_eDd89im3eEwKEP99k1XCNtVP","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Integrate emit_incident into agent-watchdog skill\n\nYou are a specialized sub‑agent responsible for updating the `agent‑watchdog` skill to use the unified incident emitter (`emit_incident.py`) from the `error‑learning‑loop` skill.\n\n### Context\nThe `agent‑watchdog` skill currently writes incidents directly to `ERRORS.md` via the `append_to_errors` method in `watchdog_orchestrator.py`. It also attempts to trigger the learning loop via `trigger_learning_loop` (which either spawns the error‑learning‑loop skill or runs `update_index.py` as a fallback).\n\nThe newly created `emit_incident.py` (located at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error‑learning‑loop/scripts/emit_incident.py`) provides a unified interface for logging incidents and optionally triggering the learning loop. It writes incidents in the correct Pattern‑Key format and ensures consistency.\n\n### Goal\nModify the `agent‑watchdog` skill so that it calls `emit_incident` instead of writing directly to `ERRORS.md`. This will ensure all incidents are processed through the same pipeline and benefit from automatic deduplication, guardrail promotion, and reconciliation.\n\n### Requirements\n1. **Preserve existing functionality**: The watchdog must still be able to log stalls, deadlocks, and other incidents with the same telemetry fields (model, stall_duration, recovery_level, success, runtime_type, task_type, items_count).\n2. **Use the unified emitter**: Replace the `append_to_errors` method (and any other direct writes to `ERRORS.md`) with a call to `emit_incident`.\n3. **Maintain trigger logic**: The watchdog currently calls `trigger_learning_loop` after appending an incident. Since `emit_incident` can trigger the learning loop automatically (default `trigger_learning=True`), you may either:\n   - Keep the trigger call as a fallback (optional)\n   - Remove it to avoid duplication (recommended)\n4. **Handle imports**: Decide whether to import the `emit_incident` function from the error‑learning‑loop script or call it as a subprocess. The `emit_incident.py` script provides both a Python function and a CLI.\n5. **Update any helper functions**: The `watchdog_learning_adapter.py` generates incident dicts with pattern keys. Ensure the pattern‑key format matches the new system (already compatible: e.g., `model|STALL|{model}|no_response|runtime_stuck`).\n6. **Test the integration**: After making changes, run a quick test to verify incidents are still logged correctly and the learning loop is triggered (if enabled).\n\n### Steps\n1. Examine the current `watchdog_orchestrator.py` and `watchdog_learning_adapter.py`.\n2. Determine the best way to call `emit_incident`:\n   - Option A: Import the function directly (requires adding the error‑learning‑loop scripts directory to `sys.path`).\n   - Option B: Call the script via `subprocess.run`.\n   - Consider dependencies and simplicity.\n3. Modify `append_to_errors` (or replace it) to call `emit_incident` with the appropriate parameters:\n   - `pattern_key` (from incident dict)\n   - `severity` (default 'S2' for stalls, maybe 'S1' for deadlocks?)\n   - `source_skill` = 'agent‑watchdog'\n   - `description` = brief symptom (e.g., 'Model stall detected')\n   - `evidence` = concrete detail (e.g., 'Stall duration: 120s, recovery level: 1')\n   - `incident_type` = 'ERROR' or 'TOOL_FAILURE'?\n   - `trigger_learning` = True (default)\n4. Remove or adjust the `trigger_learning_loop` call if redundant.\n5. Ensure any other direct writes to `ERRORS.md` are also updated.\n6. Run a quick validation:\n   - Simulate a stall incident (maybe by calling the updated method with test data) and verify that `ERRORS.md` is updated with the correct format.\n   - Check that the learning loop is triggered (you can look for updated timestamps in `INDEX.md`).\n\n### Deliverables\n- Updated `watchdog_orchestrator.py` (and any other modified files).\n- A brief test report (printed to stdout).\n- Handoff report as per template.\n\n### Handoff Report Template\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=...; SEV=...] <symptom> (evidence: ...)\n- **Files touched**: <list>\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp>\n  - progress_marker: <current step>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".","label":"watchdog-integrate-emit-incident","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":47389,"output":2050,"cacheRead":21376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70815,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772813463188}}
