{"type":"message","id":"5e4ba8ad","parentId":"bd1118a3","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:12:51.739Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guardar session_key y run_id para monitoreo. Ahora registrar con watchdog. Voy a crear un script de registro rápido. Primero, necesito importar el módulo watchdog_orchestrator? Pero puedo usar el script existente register_watchdog.py y modificarlo para múltiples sesiones. Mejor crear una función simple.\n\nVoy a crear un script python que registre esta sesión. Pero también necesito registrar las próximas sesiones. Haré un archivo temporal.\n\nPrimero, obtener el session_id y run_id de la respuesta. childSessionKey es \"agent:main:subagent:f91e35bd-6a40-4b8b-a157-a198c994f1f0\". runId es \"66438eab-11ed-47af-b8a2-22fd252b4ff0\".\n\nAhora registrar. Usaré el mismo método que antes, pero con el nuevo watchdog_orchestrator. Voy a escribir un script rápido.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_M8wwv3g25GPpNccj2CvP0tXR","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/register_watchdog_multi.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport sys\nsys.path.append('/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts')\nfrom watchdog_orchestrator import AgentWatchdog\n\ndef register(session_id, run_id, task_desc, expected_runtime=10, model='deepseek-reasoner', runtime_type='subagent'):\n    watchdog = AgentWatchdog()\n    session = watchdog.register_session(\n        session_id=session_id,\n        run_id=run_id,\n        task_description=task_desc,\n        expected_runtime=expected_runtime,\n        model=model,\n        runtime_type=runtime_type\n    )\n    print(f\"Registered session {session_id}\")\n    watchdog.update_activity(session_id)\n    print(\"Activity updated\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Map of session_id -> task description\n    sessions = {\n        'agent:main:subagent:f91e35bd-6a40-4b8b-a157-a198c994f1f0': 'Integrate emit_incident into agent-watchdog skill',\n        # will add more as spawned\n    }\n    for sid, task in sessions.items():\n        # run_id unknown; we'll just use sid as run_id? but we have separate run_id.\n        # We'll need to store run_id mapping. For now, just use session_id as run_id.\n        register(sid, sid, task)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":47333,"output":795,"cacheRead":21440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69568,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772813539594}}
