{"type":"message","id":"6bb89873","parentId":"48580d2a","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:17:36.551Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_voxYoQPVuYPHtICtVlpEyFXS","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nEmit incidents to .learnings/ERRORS.md and trigger error‑learning‑loop or update_index.py.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nWORKSPACE = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace\")\nERRORS_PATH = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \".learnings\", \"ERRORS.md\")\nLEARNINGS_PATH = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \".learnings\", \"LEARNINGS.md\")\nINDEX_PATH = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \".learnings\", \"INDEX.md\")\n\ndef ensure_learning_dirs():\n    \"\"\"Ensure .learnings directory and files exist.\"\"\"\n    os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(ERRORS_PATH), exist_ok=True)\n    for path in [ERRORS_PATH, LEARNINGS_PATH, INDEX_PATH]:\n        if not os.path.exists(path):\n            with open(path, 'w') as f:\n                f.write(\"# \" + os.path.basename(path).replace('.md', '') + \"\\n\\n\")\n\ndef emit_incident(pattern_key: str, symptom: str, evidence: str,\n                  incident_type: str = \"ERROR\", severity: str = \"S2\",\n                  pattern_hint: Optional[str] = None,\n                  prevention_rule: Optional[str] = None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Append an incident block to ERRORS.md.\n    \n    Args:\n        pattern_key: e.g., \"tokens|BUDGET|token_budget|input_overflow|truncate_required\"\n        symptom: brief symptom description\n        evidence: 1‑line concrete detail (no secrets)\n        incident_type: ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF\n        severity: S1|S2|S3|S4\n        pattern_hint: optional Pattern‑Key (if different)\n        prevention_rule: optional 1‑line rule\n    \"\"\"\n    ensure_learning_dirs()\n    \n    # Format incident block\n    lines = [\n        f\"- [TYPE={incident_type}; SEV={severity}] {symptom} (evidence: {evidence})\"\n    ]\n    if pattern_hint:\n        lines.append(f\"  Pattern hint: {pattern_hint}\")\n    else:\n        lines.append(f\"  Pattern hint: {pattern_key}\")\n    if prevention_rule:\n        lines.append(f\"  Prevention rule: {prevention_rule}\")\n    \n    block = \"\\n\".join(lines)\n    \n    # Append to ERRORS.md\n    with open(ERRORS_PATH, 'a') as f:\n        f.write(block + \"\\n\\n\")\n    \n    print(f\"Incident emitted: {symptom}\")\n    \n    # Try to trigger error-learning-loop skill\n    if trigger_error_learning_loop():\n        print(\"Triggered error-learning-loop.\")\n    else:\n        # Fallback: run update_index.py\n        run_update_index()\n    \n    return True\n\ndef trigger_error_learning_loop() -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Attempt to invoke the error-learning-loop skill.\n    Returns True if successful.\n    \"\"\"\n    skill_path = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \"skills\", \"error-learning-loop\")\n    if not os.path.exists(skill_path):\n        return False\n    \n    # Look for a script that can be called\n    script = os.path.join(skill_path, \"scripts\", \"learning_loop.py\")\n    if os.path.exists(script):\n        try:\n            subprocess.run([sys.executable, script], check=False, timeout=30)\n            return True\n        except (subprocess.SubprocessError, FileNotFoundError):\n            pass\n    \n    # Alternatively, we could spawn a sub‑agent via OpenClaw tooling,\n    # but for simplicity we just return False.\n    return False\n\ndef run_update_index():\n    \"\"\"Run update_index.py to refresh INDEX.md.\"\"\"\n    # First try the error-learning-loop skill's update_index.py\n    skill_script = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \"skills\", \"error-learning-loop\", \"scripts\", \"update_index.py\")\n    if os.path.exists(skill_script):\n        try:\n            subprocess.run([sys.executable, skill_script, WORKSPACE], check=False, timeout=30)\n            print(\"Updated INDEX.md via error-learning-loop.\")\n            return\n        except (subprocess.SubprocessError, FileNotFoundError) as e:\n            print(f\"Skill script failed: {e}\")\n    \n    # Fallback to .learnings/update_index.py (legacy)\n    index_script = os.path.join(WORKSPACE, \".learnings\", \"update_index.py\")\n    if os.path.exists(index_script):\n        try:\n            subprocess.run([sys.executable, index_script], check=False, timeout=30)\n            print(\"Updated INDEX.md via legacy script.\")\n        except (subprocess.SubprocessError, FileNotFoundError):\n            print(\"Failed to run update_index.py.\")\n            update_index_fallback()\n    else:\n        update_index_fallback()\n\ndef update_index_fallback():\n    \"\"\"Fallback index update: just add a timestamp note.\"\"\"\n    ensure_learning_dirs()\n    with open(INDEX_PATH, 'a') as f:\n        f.write(f\"- Incident logged at {time.ctime()}\\n\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Test emission\n    emit_incident(\n        pattern_key=\"planning|OVERLOAD|decompose|prompt_too_long|required\",\n        symptom=\"Prompt too long\",\n        evidence=\"token_estimate=4500, max=4000\",\n        incident_type=\"ERROR\",\n        severity=\"S2\",\n        prevention_rule=\"Decompose prompts exceeding MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS.\"\n    )"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772813856540}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfb02700","parentId":"6bb89873","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:18:36.304Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Este skill ya tiene su propia función emit_incident que escribe en ERRORS.md y luego intenta trigger error-learning-loop. Esto es similar a lo que necesitamos, pero debería usar el nuevo emit_incident.py unificado. Así que hay que modificar learning_emit.py para que use el nuevo emisor.\n\nAdemás, puede haber otros scripts que llamen a esta función. Necesitamos actualizar learning_emit.py.\n\nAhora lanzar sub-agente para long-prompt-orchestrator.\n\nPero también hay que considerar otros skills como healthcheck, openai-image-gen, etc. No son críticos. El usuario dijo \"skills críticos\". Asumiré que estos cinco son suficientes: agent-watchdog, salesforce-architect, salesforce-code-auditor, long-prompt-orchestrator. Workspace-janitor también podría ser crítico, pero no tiene incidentes. Podríamos agregar integración para que emita incidentes cuando falla la limpieza. Pero lo dejaré para después.\n\nAhora lanzar sub-agente para long-prompt-orchestrator.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7nDn5Qq5R2GOWKuthb9IHrPP","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Integrate emit_incident into long-prompt-orchestrator skill\n\nYou are a specialized sub‑agent responsible for updating the `long‑prompt‑orchestrator` skill to use the unified incident emitter (`emit_incident.py`) from the `error‑learning‑loop` skill.\n\n### Context\nThe `long‑prompt‑orchestrator` skill currently writes incidents via a custom `emit_incident` function in `learning_emit.py`. This function writes directly to `ERRORS.md` using a custom format (incident block with TYPE/SEV, pattern hint, prevention rule). It also attempts to trigger the error‑learning‑loop skill or runs `update_index.py` as a fallback.\n\nThe newly created `emit_incident.py` (located at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error‑learning‑loop/scripts/emit_incident.py`) provides a unified interface for logging incidents and optionally triggering the learning loop. It writes incidents in the correct Pattern‑Key format and ensures consistency.\n\n### Goal\nReplace the custom `emit_incident` function in `learning_emit.py` with a call to the unified emitter. This will ensure all incidents are processed through the same pipeline and benefit from automatic deduplication, guardrail promotion, and reconciliation.\n\n### Requirements\n1. **Preserve existing API**: The function signature `emit_incident(pattern_key, symptom, evidence, incident_type=\"ERROR\", severity=\"S2\", pattern_hint=None, prevention_rule=None)` should remain unchanged so that existing code continues to work.\n2. **Use the unified emitter**: Inside the function, call the new `emit_incident` (either by importing the function or by subprocess). Map the parameters appropriately:\n   - `pattern_key` (already matches Pattern‑Key format)\n   - `severity` (already S1–S4)\n   - `source_skill` = 'long‑prompt‑orchestrator'\n   - `description` = symptom (brief)\n   - `evidence` = evidence (concrete detail)\n   - `incident_type` = incident_type (ERROR, NEAR_MISS, etc.)\n   - `trigger_learning` = True (default)\n   - Additional fields: `pattern_hint` and `prevention_rule` can be passed as tags or extra metadata. The unified emitter may not support them directly; you can include them in the description or as additional parameters (check the unified emitter's API).\n3. **Remove direct file writing**: The current function writes directly to `ERRORS.md`. Replace that with the call to the unified emitter.\n4. **Remove trigger logic**: The current function calls `trigger_error_learning_loop` and `run_update_index`. Since the unified emitter can trigger the learning loop automatically, you can remove these calls (or keep them as fallback if you prefer).\n5. **Handle imports**: Decide whether to import the `emit_incident` function from the error‑learning‑loop script or call it as a subprocess. Consider adding the error‑learning‑loop scripts directory to `sys.path`.\n6. **Test the integration**: After making changes, run a quick test to verify incidents are still logged correctly and the learning loop is triggered (if enabled). You can run the `__main__` block of `learning_emit.py` (which currently emits a test incident) to test.\n\n### Steps\n1. Examine `learning_emit.py` and locate the `emit_incident` function.\n2. Determine the best way to call the unified emitter:\n   - Option A: Import the function directly (requires adding the error‑learning‑loop scripts directory to `sys.path`).\n   - Option B: Call the script via `subprocess.run`.\n   - Consider simplicity and dependencies.\n3. Modify the function to call the unified emitter, preserving the same signature.\n4. Remove the direct file‑writing code (the `with open(ERRORS_PATH, 'a')` block).\n5. Remove or comment out the calls to `trigger_error_learning_loop` and `run_update_index`.\n6. Ensure any logging statements are updated appropriately.\n7. Run a quick validation:\n   - Execute the updated `learning_emit.py` (it runs a test incident) and verify that `ERRORS.md` is updated with the correct format (Pattern‑Key heading, etc.).\n   - Check that the learning loop is triggered (look for updated timestamps in `INDEX.md`).\n\n### Deliverables\n- Updated `learning_emit.py`.\n- A brief test report (printed to stdout).\n- Handoff report as per template.\n\n### Handoff Report Template\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=...; SEV=...] <symptom> (evidence: ...)\n- **Files touched**: <list>\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp>\n  - progress_marker: <current step>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".","label":"long-prompt-orchestrator-integrate-emit-incident","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1385,"output":1720,"cacheRead":61184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64289,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772813856552}}
