penclaw  3914 Mar  5 21:23 context_monitor.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  5193 Mar  5 16:23 decompose.py\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw   691 Mar  6 11:24 integration_report.md\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  2833 Mar  6 11:20 learning_emit.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  7872 Mar  5 21:29 memory_router.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw 19958 Mar  5 21:44 orchestrate.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw 12371 Mar  5 21:31 orchestrate.py.backup\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  6275 Mar  5 16:27 recovery.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  5647 Mar  5 21:26 semantic_context_search.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  7520 Mar  5 21:25 semantic_index_builder.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  7779 Mar  5 21:28 session_manager.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  5757 Mar  5 21:27 task_state_manager.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  6141 Mar  5 16:24 todo.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  5813 Mar  5 16:24 token_budget.py\n-rwxrwxr-x 1 openclaw openclaw  4002 Mar  5 16:25 validate.py","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772814613833}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d2f3c90","parentId":"4f491e82","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:31:04.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El script \"context_cleanup.py\" suena apropiado para limpiar contexto. También \"context_archive.py\" para archivar. Pero el usuario dice \"optimizar tu context\". Podría ser que quiera que use el skill para optimizar el contexto de la sesión actual, tal vez reduciendo tokens o archivando mensajes viejos. Sin embargo, yo no tengo acceso directo al contexto de la sesión más allá de los archivos. El skill long-prompt-orchestrator está diseñado para descomponer tareas largas en subtareas, no para limpiar el contexto de chat. Tal vez se refiere a usar el skill para optimizar el contexto de la conversación actual (la sesión de chat) para que yo pueda manejar mejor los tokens. Pero eso requeriría que yo analice el historial de la sesión y lo archive.\n\nMejor voy a spawnear un sub-agent para que ejecute el skill long-prompt-orchestrator en \"modo optimización de contexto\". Pero el usuario dice \"tu por tu parte ejecuta el skill de long-prompt-orchestrator para optimizar tu context\". Eso suena como que yo mismo debo ejecutar el skill. Puedo ejecutar el script \"context_cleanup.py\" o \"context_archive.py\" pasando el sessionId de esta sesión. Necesito saber el sessionId de la sesión actual. Puedo obtenerlo de session_status. Primero, voy a spawnear el agente de validación end-to-end. Luego, ejecutaré el script de optimización de contexto.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VgKh9ype7tCCH59vDAhwC7fb","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: End-to-end validation of the automated error-learning-loop system\n\nYou are an independent validation agent. Your goal is to perform a comprehensive end‑to‑end test of the newly automated learning system and produce a report with findings and improvement suggestions.\n\n### Context\nThe `error‑learning‑loop` skill has been upgraded with dual‑layer automation:\n1. **Event‑driven layer** – incidents are emitted automatically via `emit_incident.py` (used by agent‑watchdog, salesforce‑architect, salesforce‑code‑auditor, long‑prompt‑orchestrator).\n2. **Scheduled reconciliation layer** – a daily cron job (`cron_reconciliation_runner.py`) scans for unprocessed incidents and missing guardrails.\n\nAll four critical skills have been integrated to use the unified emitter.\n\n### Validation Objectives\nPerform the following steps and verify each outcome:\n\n#### 1. Event‑driven incident emission\n- Simulate a watchdog stall incident (or use the existing `test_validation.py` script in the agent‑watchdog skill) and verify:\n  - Incident is logged to `~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md` with proper Pattern‑Key format.\n  - Learning loop is triggered automatically (`INDEX.md` and `REPORT.md` timestamps updated).\n  - Incident appears in `INDEX.md` under the correct domain.\n\n#### 2. Handoff Report enforcement\n- Spawn a dummy sub‑agent that finishes **without** a Handoff Report.\n- Use `event_trigger_listener.py` (or manually check) to verify that an incident `handoff|INVALID|missing_report` is emitted.\n\n#### 3. Reconciliation scanner\n- Manually run `reconcile_incidents.py` (or `cron_reconciliation_runner.py`) with a controlled workspace copy (or use the real workspace if safe).\n- Verify that it detects missing learnings, repeated incidents, and high‑severity incidents without guardrails.\n- Confirm that it triggers the learning loop when gaps are found.\n\n#### 4. Guardrail promotion\n- Inject a repeated incident (same Pattern‑Key ≥2 times) or a high‑severity incident (S1/S2).\n- Run the learning loop (via `update_index.py` or `emit_incident` with trigger).\n- Check whether a guardrail is automatically promoted to `AGENTS.md` or `TOOLS.md` (according to promotion policy).\n\n#### 5. Cron job readiness\n- Verify the cron entry exists (`crontab -l`) and points to the correct script.\n- Simulate a cron run (by executing the command manually) and check logs.\n\n### Expected Deliverables\n1. **Validation report** (markdown) with:\n   - Pass/fail status for each objective.\n   - Concrete evidence (file snippets, timestamps, logs).\n   - Any observed issues or edge cases.\n2. **Improvement suggestions** – list of actionable recommendations to strengthen the automation (e.g., rate‑limiting, deduplication accuracy, error handling, monitoring).\n3. **Handoff Report** – use the mandatory template.\n\n### Constraints\n- Do not modify production data unless you can restore it.\n- If you need to write test incidents, use a distinct Pattern‑Key (e.g., `validation|TEST|end_to_end|test|test`) to avoid polluting real learnings.\n- Keep the test lightweight; focus on integration points, not exhaustive coverage.\n\n### Handoff Report Template\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=...; SEV=...] <symptom> (evidence: ...)\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp>\n  - progress_marker: <current step>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".","label":"validation-end-to-end-learning-system","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1115,"output":1679,"cacheRead":73344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76138,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772814613847}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae746e49","parentId":"0d2f3c90","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:31:04.639Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_VgKh9ype7tCCH59vDAhwC7fb","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:137378ff-5abc-405f-81c5-473641162967\",\n  \"runId\": \"14aea768-58c9-4d86-9d12-8dd804c65a10\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"auto-announces on completion, do not poll/sleep. The response will be sent back as an user message.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:137378ff-5abc-405f-81c5-473641162967","runId":"14aea768-58c9-4d86-9d12-8dd804c65a10","mode":"run","note":"auto-announces on completion, do not poll/sleep. The response will be sent back as an user message.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772814664631}}
{"type":"message","id":"e94ea423","parentId":"ae746e49","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:31:13.583Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ahora, ejecutar el skill long-prompt-orchestrator para optimizar mi contexto. Necesito entender qué significa \"optimizar tu context\". Podría ser limpiar el contexto de la sesión actual para reducir tokens. El skill tiene scripts como \"context_cleanup.py\" que probablemente limpia archivos de contexto antiguos. También \"context_archive.py\" archiva contexto. Podría ejecutar \"context_cleanup.py\" con los parámetros adecuados. Primero, veamos qué hace ese script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PbmQ7ESmitSe6WSzAk1ZtF1h","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/scripts/context_cleanup.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1493,"output":293,"cacheRead":74432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76218,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772814664639}}
{"type":"message","id":"536fe2c1","parentId":"e94ea423","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:31:13.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_PbmQ7ESmitSe6WSzAk1ZtF1h","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nContext cleanup: summarize, archive, update index, prune context.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\n\n# Add skill scripts directory to path\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)))\n\nfrom context_monitor import ContextMonitor\nfrom context_archive import ContextArchiver, archive_context_cleanup\nfrom semantic_index_builder import update_semantic_index\nfrom task_state_manager import TaskStateManager\nfrom session_manager import SessionManager\n\nWORKSPACE_MEMORY = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/memory\")\n\nclass ContextCleanup:\n    \"\"\"\n    Orchestrates context cleanup when threshold exceeded.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, session_id: str, run_id: str):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.run_id = run_id\n        self.monitor = ContextMonitor()\n        self.archiver = ContextArchiver(session_id, run_id)\n        self.task_state = TaskStateManager(run_id)\n        self.session_manager = SessionManager()\n    \n    def summarize_completed_reasoning(self, context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Generate a concise summary of completed reasoning steps.\"\"\"\n        summaries = []\n        for item in context_items:\n            summary = item.get('content_summary', '')\n            if summary and len(summary) > 100:\n                summary = summary[:100] + \"...\"\n            summaries.append(f\"- {item.get('id', 'unknown')}: {summary}\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(summaries)\n    \n    def extract_decisions(self, context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> List[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract decisions from reasoning (heuristic).\"\"\"\n        decisions = []\n        for item in context_items:\n            content = item.get('content_summary', '')\n            # Simple heuristic: lines with \"decide\", \"choose\", \"will use\"\n            lines = content.split('.')\n            for line in lines:\n                line_lower = line.lower()\n                if any(kw in line_lower for kw in ['decide', 'choose', 'will use', 'should', 'must']):\n                    decisions.append(line.strip())\n        return decisions[:5]  # limit\n    \n    def extract_facts(self, context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> List[str]:\n        \"\"\"Extract factual statements from reasoning.\"\"\"\n        facts = []\n        for item in context_items:\n            content = item.get('content_summary', '')\n            # Heuristic: statements without modal verbs\n            lines = content.split('.')\n            for line in lines:\n                line_lower = line.lower()\n                if not any(kw in line_lower for kw in ['could', 'should', 'would', 'might', 'maybe']):\n                    if len(line.strip()) > 20:\n                        facts.append(line.strip())\n        return facts[:10]\n    \n    def get_task_history(self) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"Get history of completed tasks from task state.\"\"\"\n        tasks = self.task_state.get_all_tasks()\n        history = []\n        for task_id, task in tasks.items():\n            if task.get('status') == 'complete':\n                history.append({\n                    'task_id': task_id,\n                    'status': task['status'],\n                    'outputs': task.get('outputs', []),\n                    'summary_reference': task.get('summary_reference')\n                })\n        return history\n    \n    def perform_cleanup(self, context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]], tags: List[str] = None):\n        \"\"\"\n        Perform full cleanup:\n        1. Summarize completed reasoning\n        2. Archive reasoning artifacts\n        3. Update semantic index\n        4. Remove obsolete reasoning from prompt (caller should clear context)\n        5. Keep only task state and next step\n        \"\"\"\n        if not tags:\n            tags = ['cleanup', 'context_optimization']\n        \n        print(f\"[ContextCleanup] Starting cleanup for run {self.run_id}\")\n        \n        # Step 1: Summarize\n        reasoning_summary = self.summarize_completed_reasoning(context_items)\n        decisions = self.extract_decisions(context_items)\n        facts = self.extract_facts(context_items)\n        task_history = self.get_task_history()\n        \n        # Step 2: Archive\n        archive_dir = archive_context_cleanup(\n            session_id=self.session_id,\n            reasoning_summary=reasoning_summary,\n            decisions=decisions,\n            facts=facts,\n            task_history=task_history,\n            tags=tags\n        )\n        \n        # Step 3: Update semantic index with this run\n        update_semantic_index(self.run_id)\n        \n        # Step 4: Increment cleanup count in session manager\n        self.session_manager.increment_cleanup_count(self.session_id)\n        \n        # Step 5: Return instructions for what to keep\n        keep_items = []\n        # Keep items that are still relevant (e.g., latest step)\n        # For simplicity, we assume all provided context_items are obsolete\n        # and will be cleared by caller.\n        \n        print(f\"[ContextCleanup] Cleanup completed. Archive: {archive_dir}\")\n        return {\n            'archive_dir': archive_dir,\n            'reasoning_summary': reasoning_summary,\n            'decisions_count': len(decisions),\n            'facts_count': len(facts),\n            'tasks_archived': len(task_history)\n        }\n    \n    def cleanup_if_needed(self, current_context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Check if cleanup is needed (via monitor) and perform if yes.\n        Returns cleanup result if performed, None otherwise.\n        \"\"\"\n        # Add items to monitor\n        self.monitor.context_items = current_context_items\n        self.monitor.current_context_tokens = sum(item.get('tokens', 0) for item in current_context_items)\n        \n        if self.monitor.should_cleanup():\n            print(f\"[ContextCleanup] Threshold exceeded, performing cleanup.\")\n            result = self.perform_cleanup(current_context_items)\n            self.monitor.mark_cleanup_triggered()\n            # Clear monitor after cleanup\n            self.monitor.clear()\n            return result\n        return None\n\ndef trigger_cleanup(session_id: str, run_id: str, context_items: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Convenience function.\"\"\"\n    cleaner = ContextCleanup(session_id, run_id)\n    return cleaner.perform_cleanup(context_items)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Example usage\n    session = \"test_session\"\n    run = \"test_run\"\n    \n    # Simulate some context items\n    items = [\n        {'id': 'step1', 'tokens': 500, 'content_summary': 'We decided to split the task into three parts.'},\n        {'id': 'step2', 'tokens': 800, 'content_summary': 'The first part is to write introduction.'},\n        {'id': 'step3', 'tokens': 1200, 'content_summary': 'We will use Python for scripting.'}\n    ]\n    \n    result = trigger_cleanup(session, run, items)\n    print(f\"Cleanup result: {result}\")"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772814673590}}
