{"type":"message","id":"ceaeb51a","parentId":"04d4fbdf","timestamp":"2026-03-06T16:42:19.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfecto. Voy a reenviar las sugerencias de mejoras al mismo agente de validación, pidiéndole que implemente las correcciones prioritarias (deduplicación y promoción automática de guardrails). Luego avisaré al usuario y procederé con la API de Gemini. Primero, necesito obtener el session_key del agente de validación que acaba de completar. Veo que el session_key es \"agent:main:subagent:137378ff-5abc-405f-81c5-473641162967\". Puedo usar sessions_send para enviarle un nuevo task. Sin embargo, el agente ya está en estado \"completed\". Podría spawnear otro sub-agente con la misma etiqueta, pero mejor usar sessions_spawn de nuevo con un nuevo run. O enviar un mensaje a la sesión existente (aunque está finalizada, puede que aún acepte). Prefiero spawnear un nuevo sub-agente independiente, pero con la misma especialización. Eso mantiene la separación de responsabilidades.\n\nCrearé un nuevo sub-agente llamado \"error-learning-loop-improvements\" con el task de implementar las mejoras identificadas. Eso mantiene el balanceo de carga: el agente de validación ya entregó su reporte; ahora un nuevo agente de implementación se encarga de los ajustes.\n\nMientras tanto, el usuario me dará la API key de Gemini para configurarla. Pero primero debo lanzar el sub-agente. Vamos a hacerlo.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7KCHZ1OInGSAGu2FPjRoq393","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Task: Implement improvements to error‑learning‑loop automation\n\nYou are a specialized sub‑agent responsible for implementing the improvements identified during the end‑to‑end validation of the automated learning system.\n\n### Context\nThe validation report revealed two critical gaps in the automation:\n\n1. **Semantic deduplication enhancement** – incidents with identical Pattern‑Keys are not merged; each creates a separate entry with `Count:1` instead of incrementing `Count`.\n2. **Automatic guardrail promotion** – high‑severity incidents (S1/S2) and repeated incidents (≥2 occurrences) are not automatically promoted to guardrails in `AGENTS.md`/`TOOLS.md`.\n\n### Objectives\nImplement the following improvements:\n\n#### A. Semantic Deduplication Enhancement\n- Modify the deduplication logic in `update_index.py` (or the shared `common.py` module) to **merge incidents with identical Pattern‑Keys** across `ERRORS.md` and `LEARNINGS.md`.\n- When merging, **increment the `Count` field** and update `Last Seen` timestamp.\n- Ensure the merge preserves all unique symptoms/evidence (maybe as a list of occurrences).\n- The merged entry should appear only once in `INDEX.md` with the correct count.\n\n#### B. Automatic Guardrail Promotion\n- Extend the reconciliation scanner (`reconcile_incidents.py`) to **detect incidents eligible for guardrail promotion**:\n  - Pattern‑Key appears **≥2 times** (Count ≥2).\n  - Incident severity is **S1 or S2** (high).\n- When such incidents are found, trigger **full learning‑loop processing** (not just index rebuild) that extracts learnings and applies promotion policy.\n- Ensure the promotion logic respects existing mitigation M1 (prevent overfitting) and writes guardrails to the appropriate file (`AGENTS.md` for workflow/coordination, `TOOLS.md` for tool‑specific).\n- Each guardrail must include:\n  - Prevention rule\n  - Trigger condition\n  - Preflight check\n\n#### C. Rate‑Limiting (Optional but recommended)\n- Add a simple rate‑limiting mechanism to `emit_incident.py` to avoid flooding `ERRORS.md` with identical Pattern‑Keys within a short window (e.g., 5 minutes).\n- Could be implemented as a per‑Pattern‑Key timestamp cache in memory or a small file.\n\n### Constraints\n- Preserve backward compatibility: existing manual and wrap‑up modes must still work.\n- Do not delete or corrupt existing learnings.\n- Keep changes minimal and auditable.\n- Test each improvement with controlled incidents (use Pattern‑Keys prefixed with `improvement_test|`).\n\n### Deliverables\n1. Updated scripts:\n   - `common.py` and/or `update_index.py` (deduplication).\n   - `reconcile_incidents.py` (guardrail promotion detection).\n   - Optionally `emit_incident.py` (rate‑limiting).\n2. A validation test that demonstrates:\n   - Two identical test incidents are merged (Count becomes 2).\n   - A high‑severity test incident triggers guardrail promotion (or at least triggers the full learning‑loop).\n3. Handoff report as per template.\n\n### Handoff Report Template\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=...; SEV=...] <symptom> (evidence: ...)\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp>\n  - progress_marker: <current step>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".","label":"error-learning-loop-improvements","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":7347,"output":1609,"cacheRead":68160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772815287387}}
